title: swedish tea ring
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and raisins.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Heat water and salt to boiling.
Add potatoes; heat to boiling. Cover and cook until tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain.
Cool slightly.
Remove skins.
Cut potatoes into fourths.
Heat oven to 375°.
Layer potatoes, eggs, onions and pimento in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk, garlic, onion salt and pepper.
Pour on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Bake uncovered until potatoes are hot and cheese is melted, about 25 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until set.

title: crisco whole egg cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coconut bon bons
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add sugar gradually and continue beating until well mixed.
Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Form into bite size balls and roll in coconut.
Chill.
Makes 40.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in shells.
Cook until firm.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: wayne's no bake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add 3 1/2 cups oats and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Mix well and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
You can add peanut butter, if desired.
Serves 2.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Put corn in saucepan and heat, then let cool.
After corn has cooled, add tomatoes, onions and cucumbers.
In bowl, mix sugar, salt, pepper and Miracle Whip together.
Then add to corn mixture. Mix well, then refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Brown pork sausage until crumbly and well done (about 20 minutes).
Add onion; saute until transparent.
Drain fat.
Add taco relish and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens. Beat together the milk, eggs and flour.
Add cheese.
Layer chilies, pork mixture, cheese and egg mixture in a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese and egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: oven fried potato slices
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put butter in 2-quart glass baking dish and melt in oven.
Add potatoes and turn to coat; bake 15 minutes and turn.
Sprinkle with seasonings and bake 15 to 20 minutes until tender.

title: apple bars
directions: Put half of dough on bottom then pie mix and other half of dough.
Top with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients except ice cubes in blender.
Turn on blender, then drop ice cubes in one by one.
Blend until smooth. Pour into glasses and serve immediately.
Makes a delicious drink that serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, margarine, milk, sugar, eggs, spices and vanilla well.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and Five-Alive juice together.
Freeze it. When ready to serve, remove from freezer about 3 to 4 hours and add Sprite or Mountain Dew.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and Italian seasoning in shallow dish.
Dip chicken breast in milk and roll in cheese mixture.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 12 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: no more pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin as can reads; put in 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Sprinkle yellow cake mix on pumpkin; sprinkle chopped nuts on top. Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cut and flip cake; serve with whipped cream on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until almost cooked.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Warm soup and milk in saucepan and pour over broccoli.
Cut cheese into strips and punch down into mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle on bread crumbs that have been moistened with melted butter.
Put back in oven until bread crumbs are brown.
May need to put under broiler for a few seconds to get brownness you desire.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain fat.
Saute with onion, water chestnuts, green pepper and celery.
Bring the water to boil; add rice and envelopes of chicken soup.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add to sausage mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Serves 14.

title: buffalo wings
directions: First, broil chicken for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine butter, Tabasco sauce and vinegar in saucepan.
Add chicken and coat evenly.
Low calorie recipe.

title: cucumber yogurt dip
directions: Blend together yogurt and mayonnaise.
Peel cucumbers.
Cut in half, lengthwise and remove seeds.
Chop cucumbers fine to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Drain well.
Add cucumber and remaining ingredients to yogurt mixture.
Blend thoroughly and chill.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine beef, water, soup and dry soup.
Bake in covered pan in 300° oven for 2 hours.
Add enough onions, carrots and potatoes for your family and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours more.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Rinse canned beans well.
Mix soup with beans.
Place in 1 1/2 quart dish.
Bake in oven at 325° until hot.
Add onion rings or grated cheese to top, just before serving.

title: tuna cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve on lettuce or on a bun for a lite lunch or supper.

title: big festive salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: split pea casserole
directions: Cook peas in 8 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Turn off and cover.
Let sit 1 hour.
Drain.
Add 2 1/2 cups water, salt, pepper, tomato juice and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Now add cabbage, carrots and potato.
Simmer covered 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Very low fat!

title: red lobster cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with spoon until soft dough forms. Beat for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Mix shortening, orange rind and juice and eggs.
Put together, then, fold in cranberries.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: egg and bacon casserole
directions: Place butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Heat at 325° for 5 minutes or until melted, tilting to coat.
Pour in croutons and set aside.

title: holiday drink
directions: Mix ingredients, bring to a boil and serve.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Arrange strawberries in a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cook mashed berries, sugar, cornstarch and water until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over berries and chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Put the following ingredients into a large mixing bowl; shortening, brown sugar, sugar, egg, peanut butter, water and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes. Add sifted flour mixture.
Beat for 1 minute.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press lightly with a fork dipped in flour to flatten cookies and make top ridged.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream oleo and cheese together; add sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour into a pie pan and bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours (start in cold oven).
Cool before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well, then refrigerate.
Cover with nuts.

title: bacon cheeseburger pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs (beaten) and can of pumpkin to mixture and mix well with electric mixer.
Sift together all other ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 2/3 cup water to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.
Freezes well.

title: honest and true irish stew
directions: In dutch oven layer half the potatoes, and then all the lamb and onions.

title: grape pie
directions: Beat
egg
slightly.
Add
sugar
and grapes.
Line pan with pastry;
add filling.
Dot with butter and cover with top crust. Bake
at
450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes or until grapes are tender.

title: easy skillet chicken
directions: Place chicken in a skillet, pour the onion soup on top. Cover and cook slowly until chicken is tender. Serve with rice.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding.
Stir in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: country ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat Velveeta, milk and Miracle Whip over low heat in a large skillet; stir until sauce is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes uncovered.

title: pumpkin vanilla pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with mixer for 3 to 5 minutes, then put in pie crust and let set 6 hours or overnight. Serve with whip cream.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with salsa.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice with sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring until dissolved.
Add the apricot Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Let cool.
Add the buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix well. Freezes well.

title: finska kakor (finnish cakes)(nut-studded butter strips from finland)
directions: Mix butter, 1/4 cup sugar and flavoring thoroughly.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Work in flour with hands.
Chill.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips 2 1/2 x 2/3 inch.
Brush tops with beaten egg white. Sprinkle with mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and almonds.
Carefully transfer to ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients except cabbage; makes 1/2 cup of dressing.
Mix ingredients together and let set.

title: hotternl vegetarian chili
directions: Cut habanero pepper into strips, but not through the stem. Wrap in a coffee filter and tie with dental floss.
This is a pepper too hot to eat alone, but has a great flavor when allowed to cook with the chili.
Be sure to wash hands, knife and cutting board.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add habanero.
Cook on high for at least 4 to 6 hours.
Overnight is fine.
The longer it cooks, the hotter it gets.
Fish out and remove the habanero before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Spread cream cheese on cooled pastry shell.
Spread lemon filling on top of cream cheese.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover and freeze until firm.

title: papa's chocolate pie
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and egg yolks.
Combine and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° until set.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Whisk yogurt and jelly, jam or preserves together in bowl. The mixture does not need to be smooth.
Spoon yogurt mixture into popsicle molds or small paper cups with a stick inserted into center.
Freeze until firm.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix all well and pat into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine in large mixing bowl the sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt; mix well.
Add flour, soda and spices; beat well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° using pan of your choice (I like to bake it in 2 loaf pans).

title: caramelized garlic sauce
directions: Heat oil in a small skillet over medium heat until nearly smoking.
Add garlic and cook, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Be careful not to let garlic burn.
Once garlic reaches blonde color, pour out immediately into a strainer.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Stir in flour and egg yolk.
Knead dough on a floured board.
Shape into pretzels.
Paint with beaten egg white and roll in sesame or poppy seed.
Grease cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes. Serve warm with mustard.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 250° for 1 hour.

title: mocha brownies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar; beat until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating constantly.
Add syrup and flour; beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 30 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Saute onion in melted margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients in large saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: two crust pineapple pie
directions: Use a 9-inch pie plate.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan; stir well. Add reserved pineapple juice; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple, butter, lemon rind and juice; stir until butter melts.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Cover with top crust.
Slit in several places.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: amish tapioca
directions: Combine fruit juices.
Add water to make 6 cups.
Heat.
Add tapioca.
Cook 10 minutes or until clear.
Remove from heat and add jello and sugar; cool.
Add drained fruit.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Fold in 1 small carton Cool Whip.

title: chocolate cream cupcakes
directions: In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and egg; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and set aside. (Line 18 muffin cups with paper liners.)

title: mushroom and cheese dip
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine until done (4 to 5 minutes). Sprinkle flour over mushrooms; add garlic salt and stir until thick.
Add sour cream and stir.
Pour into ovenproof dish and cover with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until melted and bubbly.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread slices.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer shredded chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Prepare stuffing according to package. Put on top of chicken.
Bake 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
Bake at 350°.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together butter and cocoa.
Add eggs and sugar to mixture. Blend flour, pecans, vanilla and salt into cocoa mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Cool cake.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Mix in applesauce, vinegar and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, soda and salt and add to first mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fast and easy chicken veggie soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in pot and bring to a simmer. Cook until chicken, potatoes and noodles are done. Serve.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: honey-poppy seed dressing
directions: Thoroughly blend ingredients.
Makes 3/4 cup of a sweet/sour dressing.
Great topping for fruit salads, greens and gelatin molds.
Use on coleslaw for a pleasant tasting change.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and sausage in a skillet and drain, mix with sauce and set aside.
Boil ziti noodles.
Meanwhile, mix cheeses, egg, parsley and pepper.
Add ziti and mix again.
Spread a small amount of sauce on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then spread half of cheese and pasta mix in pan, followed by half of sauce.
Then spread remainder of cheese, pasta again followed by remainder of sauce.
Sprinkle top with a small amount of reserved Mozzarella or Parmesan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain, rinse, drain and let cool.
Dice cucumbers, tomatoes, onions and green pepper.
Mix with spaghetti. Add salad seasoning and Italian dressing.
Toss well.
Chill.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
In casserole dish, layer cabbage and the hamburger.
Pour tomato soup over the top of last layer.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Spoon Cool Whip into large bowl, add pudding and blend well. Add pineapple (with juice).
Fold in marshmallows and chill.

title: creme-filled cookies
directions: With pastry blender or fork, cut butter into flour until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cream over part of mixture; toss gently with fork.
Push to one side of bowl. Sprinkle next tablespoon of cream over dry part; mix lightly.
Push to moistened part at side.
Repeat until all is moistened.
Form into ball; divide in half.
On lightly floured surface, roll to slightly less than 1/8 inch.
Cut in rounds with floured 1 1/2-inch cutter.
Dip one side of cookie in sugar.
Place sugar side up, 1/2 inch apart, on ungreased baking sheet.
With fork, prick each cookie in 4 parallel rows.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes, or until golden and puffy.
Remove at once from rack.
Sandwich cooled cookies with frosting tinted for holiday.

title: reece cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into balls. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix chocolate pieces and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: glazed carrots(4 servings)
directions: Scrub carrots and pare or scrape off skin.
Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling, salted water until almost tender when tested with a fork.
Drain and let dry.
Put butter or margarine and light brown sugar in skillet and cook until syrupy.
Add carrots and cook slowly, turning until glazed all over.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss, then top with Ott's French dressing.

title: bourbon franks
directions: In large saucepan, mix all ingredients except frankfurters. Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add frankfurters and simmer 5 minutes. Serve in chafing dish.

title: creamed peas
directions: Drain juice from peas into pan.
Mix flour with a little water to make a smooth, thin paste.
Thicken pea juice with flour mixture.
Cook about 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour in peas.
Add sliced or cubed cheese, according to taste.
Just before serving, add cream and a little salt and pepper; possibly a little butter.

title: braised tarragon chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Heat oil in a large skillet. Add chicken and cook over medium-high heat, searing about 12 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken and keep warm.

title: pie plate pastry
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into 9-inch pie plate.
Combine oil and milk in measuring cup; beat with a fork until blended.
Pour over flour mixture.
Mix with a fork until all flour is moistened. With fingers, press mixture firmly against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Make small edge on rim of plate; flute.
Do not form a high edge.
Spoon or pour in filling.

title: betty's yum yum bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on bread.
Bake on cookie sheet at 450° until bubbly.
To freeze, let cool first.
Mixture can be kept at least one week in Tupperware.

title: flank steak(teriyaki barbecue)
directions: Combine first 7 sauce ingredients and pour over steak. Marinate 4 hours to 2 days; turn occasionally.
Barbecue over hot coals.
Baste occasionally with marinade.
Carve thin on diagonal. Serves 4.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Add enough flour to make a stiff dough to the sweet milk, white sugar, butter and baking powder.
Drop by spoonfuls into sauce.

title: scott's mexican chili beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, combine cooked beef, beans, onion, bell pepper, garlic salt and chili powder.
Let simmer.

In a bowl, put stewed Mexican-style tomatoes and green chilies, then mix together with your hands until well blended. Add mixture to beans and cook on medium heat for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pepperoni hot dish
directions: Place potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger and put in the potatoes.
Heat Cheddar cheese soup and milk and pour over hamburger.
Dot with butter and salt.
Mix the tomato soup, oregano, sugar and onion and pour over top.
Place sliced pepperoni over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn down to 350° for an hour or until potatoes are done. Top with Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese and return to oven a few minutes to melt.

title: margie's calico bean salad
directions: Using a covered pot or pressure cooker, simmer the black beans, white beans and pinto beans separately in seasoned water until tender.
Drain and reserve each type of cooked bean separately until cool.
Before combining the beans, drain any remaining liquid from the navy and pinto beans.
Rinse the black beans and drain well.

title: pistachio dream
directions: Mix dry pudding into other ingredients.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Serve as a dessert or salad.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Melt oleo and combine with sugar, Karo and salt.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and nuts.
Bake at 200° for 45 minutes uncovered.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets.
Break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: rabbit manhattan
directions: Cut up rabbit into serving size pieces.
Shake the meat in a paper bag with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in margarine.
Mix bacon, onion and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture into a baking dish and arrange rabbit meat on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: parsnip pie
directions: Beat all other ingredients together until smooth, reserving the 2 additional tablespoons of honey.
Pour the parsnip filling into the partially baked pie shell and drizzle the remaining honey over the top.
Bake at 375 for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: italian lasagne
directions: Saute meats in 4 tablespoons oil until brown; add onion, garlic, bay leaf and basil. Cook until onion is lightly browned. Add mushrooms, tomatoes, tomato sauce, 1 tablespoon salt and pepper. Simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes, adding water if necessary.

title: teenage sloppy joes
directions: Combine beef, green peppers and onion in skillet until brown. Add mixed oats, flour, salt and water with barbecue sauce and cook until done.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated until baking time.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, salt, water and syrup until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites until real firm.
Slowly pour mixture over egg whites and beat.
Add vanilla and beat until fairly thick.
Add nuts and drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Blend vinegar, salt, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed and celery seed.
Boil in a saucepan.
Put sliced cucumbers in a gallon jar and onions.
Pour mixture into a jar over cucumbers and onions. Cool and then put in refrigerator and keep.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: stromboli
directions: Let dough thaw and rise 4 to 5 hours.
Roll bread into rectangular shape, 12 x 18-inches.
Beat eggs and add oregano. Spread over bread dough.
Save a little to brush on top of loaf. Layer pepperoni, Provolone and Mozzarella onto rolled out bread dough.
Roll up into a loaf.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: tortellini with cream sauce
directions: This is the easiest recipe you'll ever find for Italian cooking at its best.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples and water until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and butter (do not melt butter).
Stir together.
Heat to boil in thick boiler.
Boil for 4 1/2 minutes.
Do not stir after it starts boiling.
Maintain a rolling boil, but do not burn.
Place in sink of cold water; add flavoring.
Stir until icing begins to thicken.
Spread on layers. If icing becomes too thick, add a little water.
Will ice four layers.

title: heath candy
directions: Melt butter and margarine; add sugar, water and corn syrup. Cook to 300°.
Pour candy out on ungreased cookie sheet, then crack.

title: orange sherbet jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Cool slightly and add sherbet.
Stir until melted.
Add other ingredients (except banana) and chill.
Add banana just before serving.
Serve on lettuce.

title: pumpkin cake (in a jar)
directions: Bake in wide-mouth canning jars that have been greased.
Fill jars only half full.

title: frog eye salad
directions: In small sauce pan mix sugar, flour and salt. Stir in pineapple juice and egg. Cook over moderate hear, stirring constantly until thickened. Add lemon juice. Set aside and cool.

Cook Acini pasta according to package directions. Combine cooked mixture with the pasta. Cover, place in refrigerator until chilled. Combine remaining ingredients, stir lightly. Chill at least one hour before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: white fruit cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add sifted dry ingredients and water alternately.
Add nuts, cherries and pineapple.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites last.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, salt and butter.
Cook slowly while popcorn is popping.
Pour molasses mixture over corn and shape into balls.

title: almondine broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli lightly until crisp.
Combine all ingredients except broccoli.
Put into oiled 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cover with Sesame Almond Topping.

title: tallerine
directions: Cook egg noodles.
Set aside.
Brown meat and onions, then drain.
Pour in 2 cans of soup.
While cooking meat and tomato mixture, cook corn and chopped pepper in a separate pan with some butter.
Combine mixtures and egg noodles.
Grate cheese in a separate bowl.
Put meat and noodle mixture in a casserole dish; add grated cheese on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: linda's ting-a-lings
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips together.
Take off heat.
Add peanuts and chow mein noodles; mix.
Spoon on waxed paper.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and pour into the unbaked pie shells.
Combine the last 5 ingredients to make a crumbly mixture; sprinkle on top of the pies.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: killer kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa into 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Place in skillet with just enough water to cover bottom of skillet.
Cook over medium heat until kielbasa is hot.
Add tomatoes with liquid, oregano and garlic.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Add sour cream, stirring to combine.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until sauce starts to thicken.
Serve over hot egg noodles or rice.

title: cheesecake
directions: Place cream cheese in mixer and cream.
Add sugar and mix well, scraping the sides and bottom of bowl often.
Add the whole eggs, egg yolks and salt, scraping the sides and bottom often.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in 10-inch pan lined with paper.
Grease and flour the sides.
Crust is not used.

title: monnie's kraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar; boil and set aside to cool.
Mix with other ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade face paint
directions: Stir together the cornstarch and cold cream until well blended.
Add water and stir.
Add food coloring, one drop at a time until you get desired color.

title: old fashioned rhubarb pie
directions: Beat egg. Beat in sugar, flour and salt and turn into plate lined with pastry. Add the butter in bits here and there, cover and finish as ordinary apple pie. I use a lattice crust. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 35-40 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift together salt, flour, baking powder and sugar.
Mix in milk and egg. Cook batter in 1-inch of hot oil.
Can be put into pan with a funnel or simply with a ladle.

title: strawberry frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too thick, add a little canned milk for spreading.
Spread on cake.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Arrange in ungreased 9-inch square baking dish.
In a bowl, combine rest of ingredients and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits rise to top and are golden brown.

title: betty rinehart's 2 minute cookies
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes (after it boils hard). Add oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: hidden jewels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan. Beat in bowl with rotary beater the egg yolks.
Stir in the brown sugar, water and vanilla. Stir in another bowl the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut up the gumdrops. Mix dry ingredients into egg mixture.

Stir in the gumdrops and the walnuts. Beat in small bowl with rotary beater until stiff, but not dry the egg whites. Stir into dough. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 20 minutes. Cut into bars. Makes 3 dozen.

title: quick supper #2
directions: Heat olive oil.
Saute onion, garlic and celery.
Add seasoning, mushroom soup, milk and water.
Add cheese (cut up). Add tuna.
Layer peas in bottom of casserole pan.
Dot with butter.
Layer drained macaroni.
Pour cheese-tuna mixture over macaroni.
Additional strips of cheese can be put on top.
Heat in oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together first.
Then add bananas, eggs and oil.
Mix together until mixture is completely without clumps. Add poppy seed according to what you prefer.

title: homestyle barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and use for all your barbecue needs.

title: yellow-gold punch
directions: Light oven; get out utensils and ingredients.
Remove blocks and toy autos from table.
Grease pan; crack nuts.

title: melon compote
directions: Place melon chunks in a pretty glass bowl.
Mix partially thawed limeade with 3/4 cup water.
Pour oven melon chunks. Garnish with mint sprigs or curls of lime peel.
This may be used as a simple dessert or as a side dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread.
Put in bottom of oblong pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Break up sausage, cook, drain and put over bread cubes. Beat eggs.
Mix with salt, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over sausage.
Put grated cheese on top.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: green salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss gently. Place green onions around edge of bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and water with Kool-Aid according to the directions on the package.
Add the remaining ingredients and freeze.
Add ginger ale when served.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine everything except yolks and vanilla in saucepan.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Stir half of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Mix well. Pour back into saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: tomato and bacon spread
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the softened cream cheese, mustard and celery salt.
Stir in bacon, tomato and green pepper. Cover and chill.
Serve with vegetable dippers.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix well and add Rice Krispies last. Mix by
hand and pinch off balls; press down with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Add 2 1/2 cups boiling water to soup mix.
Cover and simmer for 7 minutes.
In a skillet, melt the butter and saute diced onion.
Remove onion and blend in flour.
Stir in hot soup and cook until thickened.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over medium heat in a heavy pan until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Turn out and knead.
Careful, it's still hot!

title: ham cream cheese ball
directions: Mix well; form into a ball.
Leave enough ham to roll in. Store in refrigerator.

title: christmas jello
directions: Dissolve first 3 Jell-Os with 1 cup boiling water in pie plates.
Refrigerate.
Dissolve 1 cup boiling water, wine and sugar with black-cherry Jell-O in bowl; refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken n rice
directions: Simmer chicken, garlic and 1/2 teaspoon salt in water for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove chicken.
Reserve 2 cups stock.
Debone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook rice in oil on low heat.
Stir until golden brown.
Stir in reserved stock, chicken, picante sauce, cumin, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat, simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and green onions.
Continue to cook on low until most of liquid is absorbed. Serves 6.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In a stockpot, add carrots to chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Add salt, garlic, tomatoes, cilantro and onions.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve chicken in bowls, ladling broth about 3/4 full over chicken.
Sprinkle tortilla chips and cheese with the avocados last.

title: easy gnocchi
directions: Mix together to form dough.
Form into small logs.
Pinch in center.
Drop into boiling water.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain. Serve with your favorite sauce.

title: broccoli bacon salad
directions: Mix with the dressing.

title: fast oatmeal chip cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine first 4 ingredients, mix well. Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream sugars, butter and peanut butter.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Stir into mixture.
Roll into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
When done, remove from oven and top with Hershey's Kisses.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix pudding by directions on box.
Add all the other ingredients except cookies, then mix well.
Put half of the cookies on bottom, then add pudding mixture.
Top with the other half of crushed cookies.
Refrigerate to set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, then add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add zucchini; don't use electric mixer when adding zucchini.
Add nuts, flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
Mix thoroughly.

title: "garden fresh" vegetable soup
directions: Simmer bones in water with bouillon for 2 hours.
Remove bones from broth extracting the marrow.
Add chuck and simmer 1 hour, then add all the vegetables (fresh or frozen).
Vegetables may vary according to individual preference, then add rice and simmer for 45 minutes.
Then add salt and pepper to taste.
Slowly sprinkle corn meal in soup to thicken.
Add Tabasco.
Simmer 15 minutes more.
Serve with congealed salad, corn bread or hard rolls.
This is a complete meal.
Keeps 3 to 4 days when refrigerated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine the first eight ingredients.
Crumble beef over mixture and mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls, place in 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered, at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Meanwhile combine the sauce ingredients.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese while it is cold.
Bring all ingredients to room temperature; mix together.

title: broccoli with cheese and mustard sauce
directions: Steam broccoli until tender-crisp.
Place immediately in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ovenproof dish.
Mix yogurt and mustard in a small bowl and spread it over the broccoli.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place under a hot broiler until bubbly and browned. Serve hot.
Makes about 5 servings, 127 calories per serving if you use only low-fat yogurt.
Contains 142 calories per serving if you use yogurt and sour cream.

title: hand lotion(cool as a cucumber)
directions: Will need medium-size bowl, soft cloth or handkerchief, grater, spoon and tiny jar with lid.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Cook and stir first 5 ingredients over medium heat until thickened.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Cool before frosting. Spread between layers and on top.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil
and
debone
chicken.
Saute
chopped
celery and onion in	oleo.
Add strained vegetables, chicken and chicken soup. Simmer
on	low heat on top of stove until pie crust is made.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and soda.
Add milk, cream-style corn, margarine and eggs.
Meanwhile, brown meat with onions and jalapenos; drain.
Grease pans (three 8-inch square or one 8-inch square and one 13 x 9-inch rectangular).
Pour half of batter into pans. Top with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese mixture. Pour remaining batter over this.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil on high.
Stir until butter is melted.
Remove from burner and add hot syrup to beaten eggs.
Stir constantly.
Add pecans to mixture and cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla to filling.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool to cut.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat on medium heat until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat and let cool for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal. Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let harden.

title: apple dessert
directions: Cut the
apples
in half and core, slice thinly.
You do not need
to
peel the apples.
Drop slices into a bowl of cold water. Set aside.
Combine the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and
salt,
mixing
well.
Beat the egg well in a medium bowl. Stir
in
the
brown sugar, honey and vanilla.
Blend in the
well drained apples and flour mixture, mixing well.
Fold in the walnuts and raisins.
Spread mixture evenly in a greased 9-inch pie
plate.
Bake
at
for
30 minutes.
Serve hot topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: diabetic graham cracker crust
directions: Combine ingredients and press into 8 or 9-inch pan. Refrigerate 1 hour before filling.
Yields one 8 or 9-inch crust.

title: spicy oriental chicken
directions: Mix together in bowl, soy, honey, garlic, crushed red pepper and sherry.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
In nonstick skillet, heat peanut oil.
Add chicken and reserve marinade.
Cook on high heat stirring until golden brown (3 to 4 minutes), then add carrots and/or peppers.
Cook covered until vegetables are tender.
Stir in marinade and sesame oil and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly until liquid evaporates and chicken has brown glaze.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in casserole dish.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Cook to boil, stirring as needed, on stove top.
Boil 1 minute; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix crust and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes and cool.

title: chocolate pecan clusters
directions: Heat chocolate over hot water until blended.
Remove from heat and add condensed milk. Blend, then add pecans.
On waxed paper, drop mixture from teaspoon and let sit until hard. Makes 25 pieces.

title: pink peanut patties
directions: Boil peanuts, sugar, syrup and milk until it forms a soft ball.
Take off fire and stir until it loses its gloss (takes a long time).
Drop on a buttered pan or I use pot pie tins to make larger size.

title: crock-pot vegetable beef soup
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cover.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours or longer.

title: chocolatetown pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In small mixer bowl, beat butter; add eggs and vanilla. Stir together sugar and flour; add to butter mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts; pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cool about 1 hour on wire rack. Serve warm.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Pour half of the cake mixture in pan.
Mix the nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture, then rest of cake mix. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan 45 minutes.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken breasts until done.
Then shred meat off bone (or cube).
In a small amount of oil, saute onion until transparent.
Add cream cheese and cooked chicken. Cook until cream cheese is melted.
Spoon a heaping spoonful onto each tortilla.
Roll and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour Monterey Jack cheese and whipping cream over enchiladas.
You can add salsa if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo on stove and add cocoa; stir well.
Remove from heat and add remainder of ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (may need to cook longer).

title: slaw
directions: Note:
Make dressing the day before & refrigerate to enhance flavor.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop all vegetables and the eggs; mix together in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over salad just before serving.

title: chocolate surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix cake batter ingredients together.

title: holiday spiced wine
directions: Combine water, sugar, spices, orange and lemon rinds, in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Strain. Add orange and lemon juice and wine; heat gently.
Do not boil. Serve hot in pottery mugs or coffee mugs.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cook and drain broccoli. Combine corn muffin mix, onion, cottage cheese and broccoli in a large bowl. Add melted margarine and mix thoroughly. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray. Bake for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 3-quart casserole, covered, 3 1/2 to 4 hours at 325°.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Reserve 1/4 cup flour mixture.
Add remaining flour mixture alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition. Stir in flavorings.
Drizzle warm oil over walnuts in bowl.
Add reserved flour mixture; toss to coat.
Stir into batter.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until cake tests done.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll mix into walnut size balls and place on baking sheet.
Flatten each ball with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Knead together, then roll and cut.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine eggs, salt and milk.
Blend in flour.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
Cut sausage in 3/4-inch pieces. In a heavy skillet over medium heat, saute sausage.
Distribute drippings among eight 3-inch pie pans.
Pour thin layers (about 1/4-inch) of batter in each pan.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Add sausage.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake about 25 minutes or until puffed up and browned.
Serve at once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheesy potato skin appetizers
directions: Rub potatoes with oil; bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cut in half, scoop out pulp leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Cut again lengthwise. Deep fry at 375° for 2 minutes.
Drain.
Put on baking sheet, sprinkle with salt, cheese and crumbled bacon.
Broil.
Serve warm with sour cream.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Fold in blueberries. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 20 minutes. Good and moist cake.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in pieces about 2 inches in length and approximately 1/2 inch wide.
Sprinkle with tenderizer, salt and pepper.
Place in pot size of Dutch oven.
Cover with water and cook until tender.

title: chewy chocolate caramel bars
directions: In saucepan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Stir occasionally over low heat until melted.
In mixing bowl with electric mixer, beat cake mix, margarine and remaining 1/3 cup milk until dough is well mixed, about 1 minute.
Add nuts.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press 1/2 of the cake mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, pour melted caramel over and spread evenly.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on caramel layer.
Using fingers, pinch handfuls of cake mixture together and drop pieces over top.
Spread lightly with spatula to cover as evenly as possible.
Don't be concerned if the carmel is not completely covered.
Return to oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Top should be crusty, but will firm up as it cools.
Refrigerate until firm enough to cut into bars.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush all cookies, except 12.
Melt butter and pour over cookies.
Mix pudding as directed, then cream the cream cheese and pudding.
Pour over cookies and margarine.
Put Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Crush remaining cookies and spread over Cool Whip.

title: hummingbird cake(3 layer cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 5 ingredients in a bowl, then add eggs and oil.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon into 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then cool before frosting.

title: denver egg sandwiches
directions: Cook pepper and ham/Spam in tablespoon butter. Beat eggs in large bowl and add to the pepper ham mixture and stir until done. Eat as sandwich on toasted bread.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: In medium bowl beat together sugar, margarine and orange peel with electric mixer 30 seconds.
Add eggs and beat well.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Add flour mixture and milk alternately to beaten mixture, beating on low speed.
Stir in raisins, pecans and poppy seed.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: *Note:
The ham may be leftover baked ham, cubed canned ham or even Spam.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Heat pecans in moderate oven at 375° for 5 minutes.
Stir once.
Butter sides of heavy saucepan (2-quart size).
In saucepan, combine water, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Heat and stir until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Cook with stirring to soft ball stage or 236°.
Remove from heat.
Beat by hand for 1 minute or until mixture just begins to act creamy.
Add vanilla and the warm nuts.
Stir gently until nuts are well coated and mixture is creamy.
Turn out on buttered cookie sheet or wax paper.
Separate at once using two spoons or forks.

title: special k bars
directions: Boil sugar and syrup until clear.
Remove from stove.
Mix in peanut butter, vanilla and Special K.
Spread in buttered cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and butter together.
Add additional butter as necessary until mixture is spreadable consistency.
Spread over the top.

title: chocolate walnut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate over warm, not hot water, stirring constantly. Add nuts and stir.
Drop by clusters on wax paper.
Cool until set.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; cool, peel and cube.
In large mixing bowl combine potatoes, cottage cheese, sour cream, salt and onion. Place in deep casserole, greased.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy string beans
directions: Heat together and serve when cheese is melted.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine salad dressing, dill pickle and sugar.
Adjust lemon and pickle juice to taste.

title: pineapple 'n' carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine pineapple, carrot, salad oil and juice.
Cover and process 30 seconds or until smooth.
Add to ingredients in bowl mixing just until moistened.
Fold in pecans.
Grease only the bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix the first four ingredients.
Pour over chicken wings that have been placed in large cookie sheet or baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Can be reheated in microwave, but good cold also.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Add soda and salt to flour and blend.
Add flour to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Heat liquid to boiling.
Add Jell-O until dissolved.
Add dissolved gelatin.
Cool. When mixture begins to congeal add fruit and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; add drained shrimp.
Let set overnight.
Serve with corn chips.

title: fatty-fatty cake
directions: Bake cake according to package.
While still hot, poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle or drinking straw.
Pour cream of coconut over cake evenly.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Cover and refrigerate until completely cold.
Spread pie filling over cake and follow with pineapple.
Cover entire cake with Cool Whip. Sprinkle top with nuts and coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix in a 3 1/2-quart Vision Ware bowl, sprayed with no stick corn oil.
Mix in bowl as listed.

title: ground steak
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine with other ingredients. Cook until thickened.
You may serve as your meat with a meal, or make sandwiches.
Ground steak is great with slaw and tomato.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Mix dressing, oil, dill and pepper.
Pour over crackers; mix. Let sit for 1 to 2 days.

title: 6 layer dinner casserole
directions: Put the first 5 items in casserole as listed.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Pour tomatoes over all and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: real beef tacos
directions: Brown meat on both sides; add all other ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.
Add enough water to fill pan 3/4 full; don't let dry out.
Meat should fall apart.
Serve over Spanish rice or can make burritos.

title: walnut chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix mayonnaise and honey together; add chicken, celery and walnuts. (If too dry, add more mayonnaise.)
Salt to taste, if desired. Serve on bed of lettuce or use for sandwiches.

title: meat and potato squares
directions: Mix all ingredients (except potatoes and cheese).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in an ungreased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Drain off fat.

title: oven kailua pig
directions: Preheat oven to 275 degrees.

title: jello and ice cream mold
directions: Stir jello into water to dissolve.
Place jello, ice cream and 4 ice cubes into a bowl that can be sealed.
Seal well.
Shake bowl until ice cubes are melted.
Refrigerate for about an hour. Can be unmolded on a plate like jello desserts.

title: favorite casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with the onion and drain off any grease. Mix together drained corn, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and cooked noodles.
Combine with ground beef mixture.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Combine hamburger, onion, green pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Form into meatballs and brown in skillet.
Add the water, rice and vegetables.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Melt Velveeta cheese on top.

title: key lime cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1/3 cup sugar and butter to form a crust into bottom and sides of a Spring Form Pan.
Chill 45 Minutes.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar; beat again.
Sift flour with baking powder; add alternately with milk, butter, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in Bisquick, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic powder, if desired.
Put in a clean brown grocery bag.
Put chicken in bag (3 to 4 pieces at a time) and shake until well coated.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 400°; turn pieces and bake for another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: indian puris
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add cheese.
Stir in enough water to make soft dough.
Knead on floured surface about 10 minutes.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll very thin, to 16 x 10-inches on floured surface.
Cut in 2 1/2-inch circles.
Fry in deep hot fat (385°) until puffed and golden, 2 to 3 minutes, turning once. (A perfect puri resembles a fragile bubble.
Discard those which don't puff.)
Drain.
Serve warm with curry.
(They are also good plain.)
Makes about 25.

title: pecan crescent cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In a large mixing bowl of electric mixer, combine first 5 ingredients in order listed. Then add flour gradually until mixture is a putty-like consistency (you might need to use your hands to mix in the final additions of flour). Shape spoonfuls of dough into crescents or balls and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until set and barely beginning to turn golden on the edges.

title: carol's pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients, except cake mix, and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top and pour melted margarine on top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Stir the dry ingredients together.
Beat the egg white just until foamy.
Add to the milk, along with the melted butter.
Add the liquid ingredients and the zucchini to the dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, raisins, celery and nuts.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing before serving if desired.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Sprinkle with half the spaghetti sauce mix.
Spoon cottage cheese over meat.
Top with a layer of uncooked noodles and sprinkle with remaining spaghetti sauce mix, basil, parsley and salt.
Combine tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Pour over mixture, making sure all is moistened. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 35 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese over top.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: italian green beans
directions: Steam washed and cut up beans until cooked but still slightly firm.
In a big frying pan, melt butter; brown minced onion and garlic.
Add drained beans into pan; mix all around.
Add bread crumbs; mix again.

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Place dough triangles on 12 inch pizza pan - points out. Press wide ends together.
Combine ingredients - spoon onto dough. Fold points up over filling.
Tuck under in middle.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes, till browned.

title: pork and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In a bowl, combine cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Add pork cubes and stir to mix.
Add soy sauce and ginger to bowl.
Stir again to mix.
Marinate one hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and cinnamon.
Sift flour into mixture. Beat all together.
Add chopped apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread cubes in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Top with cheese. Pour egg mixture over all this.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers on bottom of bowl.
Cut bananas in slices.
Mix one package of instant vanilla pudding according to package and pour on top of bananas.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Eat!
Delicious!

title: beef international
directions: Cook round steak in 4 tablespoons of butter until all redness is gone.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Cut up onions.
Add water. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add soups, salad dressing and cooked noodles.
Add to meat; simmer.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in loaf pan or form into baking dish.
Either way pan must be greased.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: quick pepper steak
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
Heat 1 tbsp. oil in skillet. Add beef and stir-fry until browned and juices evaporate.
Push to one side of skillet.
Heat remaining oil.
Add peppers, onion and garlic and cook until tender-crisp.
Add gravy and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat through.
Serve over rice. To make slicing easier, freeze for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Add ground meat and mix.
Roll meat into a 10 x 12-inch rectangle on foil.
Place boiled ham slices and grated Mozzarella cheese on top, then jelly roll. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, put 3 slices Mozzarella cheese and 1 can tomato sauce on top.
Serves 8.

title: wiener schnitzels
directions: Beat eggs with 1 teaspoon water and set aside.
Beat cutlets and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Sprinkle a little salt on both sides of slices.
Dip in flour, then in egg, then in bread crumbs.
(Repeat for thicker schnitzels.)
Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes.
Fry in hot vegetable oil for 4 to 6 minutes on each side.
Serve sizzling hot, if possible.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, then sift 2 more times with 6 tablespoons cocoa.
Have all ingredients at room temperature, cream butter thoroughly, add sugar, then eggs one at a time beating thoroughly after each.
Add flour mixture 3 or 4 tablespoons at a time, alternately with milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Grease large angel food cake pan on sides after placing piece of wax paper shaped like pan on bottom.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Put pineapple and its
juice
in boiler.
Add jello and bring to a boil.	Let
cool.
Add other ingredients and put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter each biscuit.
Roll each one in sugar and cinnamon. Coat thoroughly and put them evenly into a greased angel food cake pan.
To make the sauce, combine margarine, sugar, vanilla and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and put on stove.
Bring to a boil, then pour over biscuits evenly.
Cook at 350° no longer than 30 minutes and immediately invert into a bigger pan (sauce runs).
Pull apart chunks and eat up.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers and onion with salt and sugar.
Mix well. Chill for several hours; drain.
Mix in sour cream, parsley and pepper.
Chill until ready to serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: parmesan potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Cook potatoes in water to cover for 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter to potatoes and mash until butter melts.
Add milk, eggs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mash until smooth.
Spoon into prepared dish.
(Can be made ahead to this point and refrigerated; bring to room temperature before baking.) Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes, until puffed and golden.
Makes 10 cups or 12 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti in the broth from the hen.
Chop and saute in butter, onions, garlic, celery and green pepper.
Combine in a large roaster, chopped hen, drained spaghetti, sauteed vegetables, pimentos, canned soups, tomatoes and milk.
Season to taste. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Drain vegetables, reserving liquid.
Combine flour and soup mix in large skillet.
Add water to reserved liquid to measure 3 cups.
Stir in mixture in skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in vegetables and beef.
Cover.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes or until heated through.
Good served over noodles or rice also.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and 2 eggs together until light and foamy.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to first mixture.
Add orange juice and rind.
Mix until smooth. Chill. roll to 1/4-inch thickness on slightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 60 cookies.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix as given.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° about 1 hour.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon stickies
directions: Mix lemon cake mix, egg and margarine together; pour into greased dish.
Cream and blend the cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar together and pour over first mixture.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: scotcharoos
directions: In a large saucepan, mix together peanut butter, corn syrup and sugar.
Cook on medium-low heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly add the Rice Krispies cereal.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13 casserole.
Press firmly to even out.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips, stirring constantly.
Pour over the Rice Krispies mixture evenly.
Cover and let stand until the chocolate and butterscotch hardens.

title: honey bear brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Blend in honey and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine flour, cocoa and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Bring to full boil; simmer for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger - cheese bake
directions: Cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Cook noodles; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, green onion and green pepper.
Spread half the noodles in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish; top with half of the meat sauce.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Add remaining noodles and meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: soured cornmeal loaves
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; set aside.
Scald milk. Pour over sugar, salt and oil in large mixing bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add cornmeal, 1 cup of the flour and softened yeast; cover.
Place in warm place (80° to 85°) about 16 hours to ferment.

title: peas and rice
directions: Slice or dice onion and fry
lightly
in
a little oil. Combine with cooked peas and rice.	Heat together and serve as a meatless entre.

title: sausage roll-ups(quick and everyone loves them!)
directions: Stir in flour to cooked and drained sausage.
Stir in cottage cheese. Add seasonings to sauce. Stir 1/2 cup sauce into sausage mixture.
Spoon some meat mixture onto tortilla and roll up. Place tortillas, seam side down, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas and bake, covered, for 40 minutes. Uncover.
Sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Cook zucchini 5 minutes in microwave, drain.
Mix remaining ingredients (except bread crumbs).
Pour over zucchini, cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and light brown.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mash salmon up.
Add egg, salt, pepper, buttermilk and flour. Shape into patties.
Fry in small amount of oil or bake at 350° until done.

title: homestead salad
directions: Cook vegetables according to package; drain. Set aside to cool. Combine celery, onion, pepper, rinsed kidney beans and mixed vegetables. Combine sugar, flour, mustard and vinegar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until clear and thick. Let cool, then stir into the vegetable mixture. Refrigerate 24 hours, stirring occasionally. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Cook sausage; pour off grease.
Add cheese; mix together then mix in biscuit mix.
Cool and roll into balls about the size of a quarter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Refrigerate. Can be covered with another package of ham.

title: cauliflower broccoli medley
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets; cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients except bacon; add to vegetables, tossing gently.
Chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with bacon. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water over medium-high heat in deep saucepan (about 2 to 3 minutes).
Pour in peanuts; stir constantly, until liquid dissolves.
The peanuts will be sugar-coated now.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the water.
Put the tomato soup into a saucepan and bring it to a boil.
Cool the soup and mix it with the gelatin.
Cream together the cream cheese and mayonnaise, and then add to this mixture the celery, onions, tuna (or salmon) and tabasco.
Combine all of the ingredients in a food processor or blender and pour into a jello mold that has been sprayed with PAM spray.
Chill several hours until firm and serve with water crackers.

title: oven-fried vegetables(mock french fried vegetables without the fat)
directions: You will also need nonstick spray coating.
Spray a cold baking sheet with nonstick spray coating; set aside.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler or microwave.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add 1 egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add other egg and beat 5 minutes.
Pour in crust and chill (use chocolate crust).

title: own crust apple pie
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon on apples and put in pie plate.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, egg, melted margarine and walnuts (if desired).
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry field salad
directions: Place spring mix in salad bowl. Top with strawberries, nuts and blue cheese. Pour vinagrette over salad, toss to coat the ingredients well and serve.

title: freezer salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 1 minute.
Combine broccoli and other ingredients in a bowl.
Add vinegar mix and toss.

title: pineapple-banana nut snack cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square cake pan.
In a large bowl, sift together the flour and baking soda.
Add cinnamon, sugar and salt. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and add oil, pineapple, eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Stir to blend, but do not use a mixer.
Fold pecans into the batter. Pour the batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 9.

title: oriental turkey burgers
directions: An all-American favorite has always been the turkey sandwich. Think of how you looked forward to having leftover turkey for sandwiches.
Instead of just once a year or so, now start enjoying this low-fat, low calorie, low cholesterol sandwich throughout the year.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix with instant pudding mix; then add oil and water. This will be thick.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Then add pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: pinch-it cake
directions: Divide each biscuit in two sections.
Roll into ball shape. Combine sugar, cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Set aside.

title: super ribs
directions: Take a rack of ribs and remove excess fat. Cut into single or double pieces. Boil for 30 minutes. While ribs are boiling, mix the rest of the ingredients in a bowl. After ribs have boiled, remove and drain. Place ribs in a casserole dish and pour sauce from bowl over them. Place in oven and bake at 350° for 3 hours. Baste every 30 minutes until sauce is gone.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cube broccoli stalks and cook in boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes; add flowerettes and cook 5 minutes more.
Drain. Separately blend soup and flour; add sour cream, carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli.
Place mixture in a casserole dish.
Combine stuffing mix and butter and sprinkle around edges of casserole.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook in large saucepan over medium heat sugar, salt, syrup and margarine until soft ball forms when dropped in water (about 5 minutes).
Add soda.
Take corn from oven where it has been kept at 200° in a large pan since popping.
Pour syrup mixture over corn and toss until all corn is covered.
Return to oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
When done, remove from oven, cool and store in plastic bags or an airtight container.

title: date cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates with baking soda in pan.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
Add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in 5 x 7-inch pan.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Make 9-inch pie shell and cool.
Mix together sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add boiling water, stir and cook over medium heat until clear.
Remove from stove and add 3 drops red food coloring and 3 tablespoons strawberry jello powder.
Mix well and cool.
Line pie shell with washed berries and add cooled mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and whipped cream.

title: 1-2-3 sugar cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix Crisco and sugar; add eggs and flavoring, mixing well.
Add flour gradually, mixing well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough onto floured surface and cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Cook on cookie rack.

title: sausage soup
directions: In large, heavy pot, combine sausage and water.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Drain and cut into thin slices; return to pot.
Add remaining ingredients, except the macaroni and vegetables.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni and cook for 5 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and cook for 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 9 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Heat to boil 1/4 cup butter in 1 cup water.
Pour over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and spread in an 8 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake until it browns.
Cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together first 7 ingredients.
Make a well in center and add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Divide into 2 or 3 greased loaf pans or 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or less for small pans.
Serve plain or with apple butter. Can be frozen.

title: rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Karo syrup on low heat.
Add vanilla wafers, pecans and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour rum over mixture and knead with hands until well blended.
Roll into marble size balls. Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: string beans
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around 6 to 8 beans.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 20 minutes.
Turn oven to 400° to crisp bacon.
Baste with brown sugar sauce in dish.
Serve 2 per person.

title: sicilian meat rolls
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix same as for regular meat loaf. On foil, pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top of meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, roll up and seal edges and place in a pan, seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Place cheese slices on top of roll and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Chop up onion and beef in food processor.
Let cheese soften and get to room temperature before mixing.
Form into ball and refrigerate.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon, 2 inches apart, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt items in top of double boiler.
Afterwards, let cool and fold in a small carton Cool Whip.
Place in baked pie shell. Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Put rhubarb in an 11 x 7 or 9 x 9 baking dish. Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, butter, baking powder, salt and milk. Spoon this mixture over the rhubarb. Mix 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough. Pour hot water over all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: mrs. mckeever's fruitsticks
directions: Mix in order (nuts, dates, sugar, flour, eggs, salt and baking powder); bake at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 30
minutes. Cut into 2 or 3-inch sticks before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix
peanut butter, milk and vanilla until well blended. Gradually add sugar.
Mix until smooth and of spreading consistency.
Makes enough frosting for 2 (9-inch) round layers.

title: diabetic banana cake
directions: Note:
Equal cannot be used as a sugar substitute.

title: squash cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: penne with mussels and shrimp
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add garlic and pepper flakes; saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, parsley and basil. Bring to a boil; lower heat and cover.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add clam juice, then shrimp.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add mussels and brandy; cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer, until shrimp are pink and mussels are open.
Meanwhile, cook pasta and drain.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Top pasta with hot sauce.
Enjoy!

title: southern cornbread dressing
directions: Prepare and bake an 8-inch square pan of Southern Style Cornbread. Cool and crumble into a large mixing bowl; set aside.

title: sausage dumplings
directions: In a skillet, crumble and brown the sausage.
Boil potatoes as for potato soup.
Boil slowly with salt and pepper.
When done, add the fried sausage.
Make dumplings as for chicken and dumplings.
Add to the potatoes and sausage.
Cook until done.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all in double boiler except vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer at high speed until blended.
Place over boiling water and beat until stiff peaks form.
Remove from boiling water, add vanilla.
Beat another minute.
Spread on cake.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill dough 3 hours.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness; cut to desired shape and bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: italian style rice casserole
directions: Heat broth and salt to boiling.
Stir in rice; cover and cook for 20 minutes, or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Meanwhile, saute ham, mushrooms and onions in oleo or corn oil or margarine.
When rice is cooked, add all remaining ingredients and mix lightly with a fork.
Heat a minute or two longer.
Makes six servings.

title: mile high pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Press well.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and sugar together; pour over other ingredients. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter together.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth texture develops.
Form small balls the size of buckeyes.
Refrigerate balls.
Next, slowly melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Using toothpicks dip cold buckeyes into chocolate until two thirds covered.
Let dry on waxed paper.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let cool.
Mix next 6 ingredients; pour in pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Top with chocolate chips, nutmeats and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham and cheese hoagies
directions: Melt margarine and add Worcestershire, onion, poppy seed and mustard.
Slice dinner rolls, put bottom half back in pan and pour half of mixture over rolls.
Add ham and cheese, then put top on and pour remaining mixture over top.
Bake until hot and cheese is melted.

title: ice cream shake
directions: Put ice cream in a cup; pour in milk and stir.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg.
Add eggs, beating until well mixed.
Add milk, raisins, rice and vanilla; stir well.
Pour into 8-inch square baking pan.
Place this in a 13 x 9-inch pan that has enough water to make 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great for leftover rice.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Roll out the pastry on a lightly floured board and using a large saucer as a guide, cut out 4 circles.
Trim any fat from the beef and cut or scrape the meat into paper-thin slices with a sharp knife.
Mix the meat with the vegetables.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, onions, celery and carrots in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Add to vegetables.
Mix stuffing as stated on box, but use 1/2 amount of liquid and use 1/2 cup margarine.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in large casserole dish and spoon in vegetable mixture.
Top with rest of stuffing mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: chicken rice chicken
directions: Spread rice in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread soups over rice and pour water over all and lay chicken on top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: a healthy drink
directions: Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.
Drink 1/4 cup every day for better health!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Add sugar and set overnight. Dissolve jello in water.
Chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: fried asparagus
directions: In a frypan, slowly melt margarine.
Wash asparagus and lay whole into frypan.
Add prepared garlic to taste, 1/2 to 1/4 teaspoon of garlic salt or 1/2 clove of garlic.
Simmer under low heat.
