Keep covered until stems are tender, approximately 20 minutes.
A delicious change from steamed asparagus.

title: biscotti di regina(italian sesame cookies)
directions: In a bowl, put flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in Crisco with pastry cutter.
Slightly beat 2 eggs, milk and anise. Add to flour mixture.
With hands knead a few minutes to form smooth dough.
Break off pieces of dough to the size of a small cigar.

title: macaroni-tomato casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Combine macaroni, tomatoes, onion salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese and bake 15 minutes.

title: hearty fish chowder
directions: Saute leek in butter in large saucepan until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in clam juice, 3 cups water, potatoes, carrots and cucumber; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are almost tender, about 15 minutes.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup water, stir into soup.
Heat to boiling; boil stirring 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer until fish is tender, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Saute garlic and onion; set aside.
In Dutch oven, saute mushrooms in small amount of oil or butter; remove from pot. Saute floured chicken pieces in small amount of oil.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons dried tarragon.
Stir chicken often to avoid sticking. When all pink is gone, add sauteed mushrooms, onion and garlic to Dutch oven.
Add broth, tomatoes (slightly chopped) and all but 1 cup of juice from can of tomatoes.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons tarragon.
Cover pot; simmer for 30 minutes.
Season with chicken bouillon cubes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tangerini
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic salt in oil.
Remove from pan and saute ground beef, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: manicotti
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in 2-quart casserole, crumble beef.
Cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes, until meat is no longer pink, stirring after 1/2 the cooking time.
Drain.
Stir in sauce, water and salt.
Cook on High for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring 1/2 way through.

title: chili mac
directions: Cook meat until done.
Cook macaroni until done.
Mix tomato sauce and whole tomatoes.
Mix macaroni, meat, chili powder, onion and green pepper.
Put in glass cooking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and put in oven.
Cook until done.

title: hamburger-vegetable casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Butter a 2-quart casserole, then layer vegetables in order given.
Sprinkle each layer with peas (do not drain) and tomato soup mixed together.
Pour remainder of peas and tomato soup on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: play dough
directions: Boil 2	cups water.
Add 1/2 cup salt.	Add food coloring and mix
well.	Remove	from
heat.
Add 2 tablespoons of alum, 1/4 cup
of
oil
and
1/4 cups of flour.
When cool, knead well. Store in a plastic bag in an airtight container.

title: american cheese
directions: Dissolve Emes jel in pan of boiling water.
Place all ingredients in blender and blend thoroughly until very smooth. Pour into mold and refrigerate.
This cheese freezes nicely and can be sliced and grated while still partially frozen.
Melts when heated.

title: egg pie
directions: Makes 2 pies.
Mix dry ingredients together first.
Bake at 400° or until set.

title: yummy cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop up pecans and fruit and add 2 cups of the flour to fruit. Mix well.

title: potato kugel
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes and onion.
Quickly stir in hot oil.
Add eggs, matzoh meal, salt, pepper and pepper sauce. Mix well.
Turn into well-greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, until browned.
If desired, serve with additional pepper sauce.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together well in large bowl and store in airtight container.
Use 4 heaping teaspoons per cup.
Just add boiling water.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over low heat for 10 to 20 minutes.
This sauce is great for chicken, spareribs or beef.

title: low calorie green beans au gratin
directions: Layer in casserole; pour tomato juice on top and remaining cheese and crumbs.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix together.
Store at room temperature in an airtight container.

title: pound cake with fruit(my christmas fruit cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and lemon extract.
Mix fruit, nuts and flour.
Pour butter mixture over this.
Put soda in water and add to other mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake in slow oven at about 250° for 3 hours.

title: spiced honey mustard
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Great as a glaze on baked ham or chicken.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into oiled and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes a large, oblong cake.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken and pick meat from bones.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Add margarine, cottage cheese, sour cream, peas and chicken to noodles.
Add 1 cup milk and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When it boils, turn to low and boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over 6 quarts popped popcorn.
Stir until well coated.
Turn onto 2 big cookie sheets and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: four week cole slaw
directions: Chop vegetables.
Combine vinegar, salt, sugar and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add to vegetables and stir well.
Pour oil over last.
Let stand for 3 days, mixing at least once a day. May be doubled.

title: megan's "salad taters"
directions: Mix in a large bowl:
potatoes, eggs, salt, pepper, celery seed, pickles and mustard.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: low-fat fried fish
directions: Defrost fish, season with salt, pepper and Seven Season saltless spices, coat the bottom of pan with oil.
Roll fish in bread crumbs to coat, place in pan, bake at 425° until golden.

title: split pea soup(microwave oven)
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4-quart casserole.
Cover with lid. Cook at High 8 to 9 minutes, and at Medium-low 45 to 50 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Peas should be tender.
Puree mixture in food process or blender.
Reheat, adding additional water, if necessary.

title: apple crunch
directions: Fill a 13 x 9-inch pan with apples to half full; cover with mixed white sugar and cinnamon.
Mix brown sugar, butter, oatmeal and flour.
Press down on top of apples.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: salsa
directions: Saute carrot with garlic until crisp-tender.
Let cool slightly.
Mix all ingredients together.
May stir in cumin (1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon) and cayenne pepper to taste.

title: easy homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in churn and churn until ready.

title: prawns in paradise
directions: Put 1 can consomme, cherry and curry powder into blender. Fill ramekins with mixture.
Drop a few (3 or 4) shrimp into each. Put in fridge; when set, pour a little consomme on top and decorate with a shrimp in center.
Let set.
Make the day before for best flavor.
Serves 6.

title: carrot muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: coconut cream candy
directions: Melt together butter, milk and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well using beaters for 5 minutes.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1-inch squares. Dip into melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper until chocolate sets.

title: sand darts
directions: Combine and blend
well the butter, flour and sugar. Roll to the size of a large peanut.
Put a nut in the center of each. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: leftover beef casserole
directions: Cut onion, celery and green pepper coarsely.
Chop beef in small cubes.
Cook beef in oil for several minutes and transfer to medium-sized casserole.
Cook vegetables in remaining oil until limp.
Add to beef with mushroom soup, water, salt and pepper. Cover and cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover.
Sprinkle sugar with Chinese noodles and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix and cook first 4 ingredients in double boiler until it coats the spoon.
When cool, add vanilla.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan and freeze. Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: waldorf salad with dried cranberries
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place nuts in pan and toast them about 10 minutes, stirring often; let cool.
Soak cranberries in 1 cup boiling water 10 minutes and drain.
Core and dice apples; do not peel them.
Place apples and cranberries in mixing bowl; add nuts and celery.

title: old-fashioned raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins and water; boil 5 minutes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Add to raisins and cook until clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and butter.
Turn into pastry-lined pan.
Cover with pastry strips.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: candy canes
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add egg, almond extract and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and salt; mix well.
Divide dough.
Blend into 1/2 of dough the red food coloring.
Twist part white and part red dough enough to make a small candy cane.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 9 minutes, until lightly brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool. Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: almond joy cake(makes 24 servings)
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed for one 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients with 1 cup of milk.
Pour into greased pan.

title: miracle fruit cake
directions: Combine in sauce pan first 5 ingredients.
Boil gently for 3 minutes.
Cool in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, fruits, peels and nuts.
Sift together flour, spices, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to fruit mixture; beating well after each addition.
Pour into 9 inch tube pan lined with greased wax paper.
Bake in a slow oven at 275° for 2 1/2 hours, or until toothpick inserted in center comes clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Wrap securely in aluminum foil or wax paper.
Store in a cool place.
Age 3 to 4 weeks to improve flavor.
Will store for 6 weeks.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar.
Cream until light.
Add applesauce, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat well by hand.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Add nuts, raisins and a few dates (optional).
Put in square baking dish, greased and floured.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fancy cherry cake
directions: Bake cake mix in round cake pan as directed on package.
Set aside to cool.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package, then add cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over cooled cake.
Put cherries on top in center of cake.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar thoroughly.
Gradually add white sugar and continue creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Combine baking powder, salt and flour.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Frost with Orange Frosting or your favorite.

title: rich fudge brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugars, Egg Beaters, melted margarine and cocoa until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Bake in square pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
When cooled, cut into squares.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except egg whites) and pour into pie shell.
Bake about 35 minutes at 350°.
Put the two egg whites with a pinch of salt into a bowl and beat until stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar and beat until sugar is mixed well.
Pour over top of pie and put back into oven for 1 or 2 minutes or until egg whites are light brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: easy stuffed manicotti
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, spinach and eggs.
Cook shells.
Stuff with cheese and spinach mixture.
Pour jar of spaghetti sauce over shells.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Arrange pineapple on the bottom of a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Stir the flour and sugar together; sprinkle over the pineapple. Drizzle the reserved juice over this; top with the cheese.
Mix the crushed crackers and oleo together; sprinkle over the cheese. Cover; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 10 more minutes.

title: lo-cal pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix eggs and pumpkin thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients. Spray muffin cups with low calorie nonstick spray.
Divide among 12 muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: egg yolk paint
directions: Beat and
put
into little container.
Add coloring and use clean water
color brush to "paint" cookies before baking. Can be used on rolls or pie crust.

title: dill pickle soup
directions: In a large pot, bring beef broth to a boil. In a small bowl, mix flour with milk.
Add to beef broth. Bring to a boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Whisk in egg yolk and butter. Add pickles and pickle juice, potatoes and carrots.
Heat through, but do not boil. Remove from heat. Garnish with shredded carrots and serve. One bowl diabetic exchange contains 1/4 vegetable, 3/4 bread and 1 fat.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water. Cook to soft ball stage.
Add butter and peanuts and cook until syrup is golden brown.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir quickly until it foams.
Pour very quickly into buttered cookie sheets.

title: dinosaurwich
directions: Spread topping about 3/4-inch thick on one cookie.
Place another cookie lightly on top.
Roll or lightly press edges in garnish.
Repeat.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Wrap to store in freezer for up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 12.

title: easy pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar and cream.
Boil to 228°, stirring all the while.
Add butter and pecans.
Cook until syrup reaches 236° or soft ball test.
Cool.
Beat until slightly thickened, but not until it loses its gloss.
Drop tablespoon size on double wax paper.
Candy will flatten out to 3 1/2-inch size.
Makes 12 pralines.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed.
Add egg, then beat.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture on low speed.
Drop heaping teaspoonful 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, until begins to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: strawberry shortcake in bucket
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces and set aside in bowl. In separate bowl, mix strawberry filling with 1/2 of sliced berries.
Save other half for garnishing the top.
Layer cake in bucket as follows:
cake, pudding, pie filling, strawberry mixture and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until all is used up.
Top with remaining 1/2 of strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: calico salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Mix Hidden Valley and mayonnaise.
Blend all ingredients together and chill.

title: glenda's candy
directions: Melt bark and mix in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let dry.
Store in covered container.

title: fruitcake squares
directions: Melt oleo in jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with crumbs evenly. Sprinkle with coconut, chopped fruit, dates and nuts.
Press down lightly to level it in pan.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 54 squares.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tapioca dissolves & rhubarb is tender.
Stir in 1 Tbsp. butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper; place in a large skillet. Cover with rice, green peppers and onions.
Again, season with salt and pepper.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil and boil for 40 seconds.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and drop on waxed paper.

title: rice pudding
directions: Scald milk and add salt and rice.
Cook over low heat until rice is done.
Stir often.
When rice is tender, add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Cook for 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle each serving with a pinch of cinnamon.

title: chili
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Saute onion, bell peppers and garlic until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Brown beef; drain.
Put onion/peppers back in skillet and add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, red pepper, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve with some Cheddar or sour cream as desired.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; set aside.
Beat 3 egg yolks and add milk.
Gradually add to first mixture, mixing thoroughly. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickens (or use double boiler).
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grate all the cheese and set in refrigerator.
Chop onions in large skillet and simmer a little, then add the meat and stir.
Cook until read is all gone.
Add picante sauce to meat skillet; stir well.
Simmer about 5 minutes. Add Worcestershire sauce, 1 teaspoon garlic salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Put all the meat mixture in large 9 1/2 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan or casserole dish.
Pour both cans of beans (undrained, use all liquid) evenly over top of meat mixture.
Scatter the grated cheese evenly on top.
Mix cornbread mix according to directions on box and pour over top of cheese.
Bake until cornbread is good and brown, about 25 minutes.
Serves about 8 to 10.

title: apricot casserole
directions: Drain apricots and put in 2-quart casserole (long flat dish). Cover with sugar and then cut oleo into pieces and lay over sugar. Break crackers into small pieces (not fine crumbs) and put on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Soak bran in boiling water.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Mix.
Add flour, soda, salt and All-Bran.
Mix and fold until all ingredients are moist.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Batter may be stored in jars in refrigerator for use when needed.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Add onion, lemon juice, some celery seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Pork should be cooked first.
Pour sauce over pork that has been cut up and bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: cat head biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and blend with lard or shortening.
Add buttermilk; mix good.
Pat into big loaf.
For each biscuit, pinch off a piece of dough about the size of a big lemon and pat it out with your hands.

title: mom's best potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, water and onions together until tender. Melt butter in a kettle.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk gradually.
Continue cooking until slightly thick.
Add rest of ingredients and heat.

title: western baked beans
directions: Brown steak and onion in fat. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix them well. Pour the mixture into a casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 4 to 5.

title: grilled catfish filets
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Place filet on single piece of aluminum foil seasoning with salt, pepper, paprika and garlic to taste.
Thinly slice lemon and squeeze lemon juice over filet. Place lemon on filet and wrap each in foil, sealing tightly. Grill on high heat for 8-10 minutes or until filet turns white.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix
first four (4) ingredients well, add eggs and rest of ingredients.
Mix
well
and drop small balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork dipped in plain sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl.
Line a 13 x 9-inch or larger pan with aluminum foil.
Be sure foil is large enough to seal tight, then pour mix into pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 dry Lipton soup.
Place chicken pieces (chicken breasts) 1/4 over it.
Salt and pepper and the other 1/2 of onion soup mix.
Seal foil tightly (at top and sides) over all.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with green vegetables.

title: cheerios treats
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs.
When mixture is cool, add flour.
Let rise.
Brush with melted butter. Bake in hot oven.

title: stuffed green pepper cups
directions: Note:
Cut off tops of green peppers and remove seeds and membranes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix and bake in the same pan.
Mix all dry ingredients, then make 3 holes for the vinegar, vanilla, oil and water.
Mix all dry and wet ingredients together until smooth.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with any frosting.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In large casserole dish layer potatoes, then celery, onions and chops twice.
Mix 3 cans soup with 3 cans water and pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: gravy
directions: May	use
chicken, cooked beef, roast beef drippings (add water to make amount).

title: layer pea salad
directions: Add in layers in order given.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Do not toss until ready to serve.

title: buttermilk coconut pie(no crust)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: impossible green bean pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Cover and cook beans in 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt until done or tender, about 5 minutes; drain.
Mix beans, mushrooms, onion, garlic and cheese and put in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: apple zucchini bread
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients and add eggs and milk.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Beat all together and add zucchini and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until done at 350°.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Mix buttermilk, oil, sugar, soda and baking powder into flour, then add yeast.
Mix as for biscuits.
Knead on a floured board. Put in refrigerator.
Pinch off as many as needed.
Bake at once in 350° oven until brown.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13-inch round pizza pan. Combine brownie mix, egg, oil and water in a large bowl.
Stir with a spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 23 to 27 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into wedges; top with scoops of ice cream and decorate with assorted fruit, then drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: fried rolls
directions: Mix yeast mixture with half of milk.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle flour on pastry sheet and knead into dough to prevent sticking.
Put back in bowl and let rise 2 or 3 hours. Pinch off and fry in deep fat.

title: virginia beach chicken
directions: Wrap each breast with bacon.
Pull apart beef and place in bottom of dish.
Put chicken over top.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together vegetables, mayonnaise, celery, onion and cheese and put in casserole dish.
Mix 1 stack of Ritz crackers (crushed) and 1 stick margarine and put on top.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbly.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: *Can substitute cherry pie filling.

title: seafood lasagne(frutti di mara lasagne)
directions: Cook seafood, butter, Pesto and white wine until seafood is barely cooked.
Put small amount of liquid from pot into bottom of lasagne pan.
Mix cheeses into pot with seafood.
Put one layer of lasagne down and one-third of sauce.
Repeat two more times.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Over low heat shake pan to dry potatoes.
Keep warm.

title: cake mix cobbler
directions: Put 1/2 box dry cake mix into bottom of cake pan which has been greased.
Spread can of pie filling over the cake mix. Sprinkle 1/2 cup water over the pie filling.
Spread other 1/2 of cake mix over pie filling.
Pour oil with the other 3/4 cup water and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kimberly's spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and green peppers.
Combine all ingredients and let simmer for approximately 1 to 2 hours to enhance flavors, stirring occasionally.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and broccoli.
Cut in small pieces.
Add peas.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing mix, sugar, salt and garlic powder. Add to vegetables and let stand a couple of hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Add cheese before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: dilled onion rings
directions: Put sliced onions in clean
quart
jar	along with dill weed. Combine remaining ingredients
in
saucepan and bring to boil. Remove from heat and pour
over onions and dill.
Cover and shake several times as
mixture cools. Store in refrigerator.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: reduced fat corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, oil and egg mixing until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients, then add cinnamon and squash.
Grease and flour pan. Bake about 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil; cool.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Divide into quart freezer containers and freeze overnight or a month.

title: hamburger plus
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide into 6 patties.
Broil or pan fry 8 minutes.
Turn and continue cooking till done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
(Whip the ingredients.) Use as a dip with cantaloupe, honeydew, strawberries, etc.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Layer bread cubes over bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread cubes.
Beat eggs well. Stir in half and half and salt.
Pour over bread/sausage mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken or turkey chow mein
directions: Combine hot water and bouillon cubes in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine the cornstarch and cold water; set aside.
Separate onion slices into rings and fry with celery in melted butter until softened.
Add drained bean sprouts, mushrooms, dissolved bouillon cubes and cornstarch.
Stir until thickened.
Add chicken cubes. Stir.
Add soy sauce, seasoned salt and pepper to taste.
Reduce heat to warm.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Beat in water.
Beat until thick.

title: sweet georgia bread
directions: Blend margarine with hot grits until melted.
Add remaining ingredients, except whipped cream.
Mix well.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice hard-boiled eggs in half long ways.
Take out yolks and mix all ingredients with egg yolks.
Put mixture into empty egg halves.

title: peanut brittle(recipe doubles well)
directions: Using 3-quart heavy pan, cook sugar, corn syrup and water to 260°, using a candy thermometer.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and peanuts, continuing to cook until temperature reaches 310°.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla and baking soda.
Beat vigorously, this will bubble up, Quickly pour in a buttered cookie sheet or foil.
Cool and break.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Take off heat and pour Jell-O in; mix well.
Let cool.
Pour over strawberries in baked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all together; chill.
Will be better if made and allowed to set overnight.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat together with rotary beater the vanilla pudding and whole milk.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into container of a 6-quart ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Yield: 6 quarts.

title: cashew cookies
directions: In bowl, mix first 9 ingredients.
Fold in cashews.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Store in container.

title: polly's egg nog
directions: Separate egg whites. Beat. Save until last. Mix pudding mix, sugar, egg yolks and milk. Pour in egg whites, nutmeg and vanilla. Stir well.

title: corn puffs
directions: Fry like French fries.

title: old settler baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain excess fat. Fry bacon; drain fat and break into pieces. Add sugars, catsup, molasses and dry mustard and stir together. Add beans. Stir before pouring in a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: applesauce bran muffins
directions: Sift and mix together first five ingredients.
Add cereal and sugar.
Mix together.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into loaf and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter or margarine, shortening and sugar. Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately to creamed mixture with egg, blended with vinegar and vanilla.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Mash down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately upon removing from oven, run a sharp knife under the cookies.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: maple walnut bars
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Add fat and mix well.
Set aside.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to egg and sugar mixture.
Add walnuts, raisins and maple flavor.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in 1 x 4-inch bars.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix well (add a little water if dough is too stiff).
Pour into muffin pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
(Do not overcook.)

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Melt the butter in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients and press into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(If you use a glass pan, bake at 325°.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Let it cool. Cut up strawberries. Combine sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat. Cool in refrigerator.
Put red food coloring in.
Pour over sliced strawberries.
Chill until firm and serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: cashew crunch
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Lightly grease foil.
Have a greased spatula ready.
Mix sugar and corn syrup in 1 1/2 to 2-quart glass measure.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, until sugar dissolves and mixture is bubbling.
Stir in cashews; microwave 3 to 5 minutes more, until mixture is a medium golden color.
Stir in butter and vanilla until butter melts.
Add baking soda, stirring thoroughly, until mixture is foamy.
Immediately pour onto prepared cookie sheet.
Spread with greased spatula to 1/4-inch thickness.
Let stand 1 hour.
Peel off candy and break in chunks.
Makes 1 pound.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, margarine and oil; beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop small balls of dough on cookie sheet and flatten slightly with fork.
If desired, sprinkle with colored or plain sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lumberjack beans
directions: Pour contents of bean can into small mixing bowl.
Dissolve instant coffee into the whiskey.
Stir well and let marinate for several hours.
Just before oven time, line a high sided casserole dish with pineapple slices.
Pour in the beans.
Bite into a couple of beans to try the flavor.
Bourbon flavor and alcohol contents will be reduced in the oven.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or more. Serves 2+.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese. Add sugar. Cream until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg. Add flour and vanilla flavoring. Beat until smooth. Bake 1 1/2 hours in greased tube pan at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break 1 pound spaghetti into 3 pieces and cook until tender. Drain well and cool.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Mix in bowl meat, eggs, 2 handfuls of bread crumbs and 3 tablespoons of Romano cheese; form meatballs.

title: crab-shrimp bake
directions: Drain all ingredients well.
Then combine ingredients except crumbs.
Place in individual seashells, in pastry shells or in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 to 25 minutes or longer if in one dish.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut each strip of bacon in half and wrap around water chestnut. Secure with toothpick.
Place on ungreased pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until bacon is crispy and brown.
Drain.

title: cream of broccoli cheese soup
directions: In heavy soup pot, add water, onion, basil, salt and pepper. Cook, covered, for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add broccoli. Continue to cook for 15 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Melt butter in microwave.
Add flour and stir to make a paste.
Whisk with hot chicken broth.
Add mixture to soup pot (this thickens the soup).
In microwave, heat milk and Velveeta until cheese is melted.
Add to soup pot.
Stir and heat thoroughly.
Do not allow soup to boil.
For thicker soup, you may remove broccoli from the soup pot and puree in food processor.
Return pureed broccoli to soup pot.

title: mushroom chili
directions: Fry ground beef or turkey, then add other ingredients and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding and pie filling(for the fifth basic food group)
directions: Use Ida Red or Rome apples or mixture of Granny Smith and McIntosh.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: Blend dry ingredients in a 1-quart jar.
Add remaining ingredients and shake well.
Store in refrigerator until needed; shake well before using.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups dressing.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat for 15 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cut vegetables to 1/2-inch pieces and cover with chicken stock.
Add marjoram, salt and pepper.
Simmer until the vegetables are cooked.
Put all ingredients through the blender. Return to saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add the cubed cheese. Heat just until the cheese is melted, but not thoroughly mixed into the soup.
Serves 4.

title: honey mustard chicken nuggets(microwave)
directions: Cut chicken into 18 (1-inch) pieces.
Combine honey, mustard, margarine and soy sauce in microwave-safe medium bowl; stir well and microwave at High for 20 seconds or until margarine melts. Add chicken pieces, stirring to coat.
Combine cornflake crumbs and paprika; dredge each chicken piece in crumb mixture, using wooden picks.
Arrange half of chicken pieces in a circle around the edge of a large, heavy-duty paper plate, cover with wax paper and microwave at High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Repeat with remaining chicken pieces.
Microwave remaining honey-mustard at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve with chicken nuggets.
Yield: 6 servings.
Each serving of 3 nuggets with sauce contains 126 calories and 2.8 gm fat.

title: streusel top rolls
directions: Mix the butter, sugar, flour and cinnamon together and set aside.
Place rolls on baking sheet and spread streusel topping on top.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until golden brown at 400°.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
At same time, thoroughly heat cream of celery soup with milk
added to it.
When heated, add Cheddar cheese (shredded) and cook until cheese melts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a well buttered casserole, layer the above in order given. Season each layer as you go along.
Mix the liquid from the peas with 1 can tomato soup and pour over all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.
Cover with foil.
Very tasty!

title: green stuff
directions: Layer 1:
Combine flour, margarine, and nuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: frosted orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add sherbet. Stir to dissolve. Cool until partly thickened. Add pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Pour into large flat cake pan. Chill until firm. Combine pineapple juice, sugar, flour, egg and butter. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick; let cool.
Stir often. Fold in prepared whipped topping mix. Spread on firm gelatin.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Heat butter and oil in a deep pan over medium heat.
Add garlic and chicken; saute until chicken is browned.
Add rosemary, salt, pepper, wine and water.
Cook slowly until chicken is tender (approximately 20 minutes).

title: mom's egg nog
directions: Separate egg whites; to egg whites, add sugar, a little at a time, while beating.
Continue adding sugar and beating until whites stand in soft peaks.
In a large bowl, pour in egg nog, slightly beaten egg yolks, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend in ice cream until melted.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Chill and serve.
Now, add favorite spirits, if desired.
Simply delicious and sinfully rich.

title: chicken royal
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except eggs.
Spread half the mixture in a casserole dish.
Add a layer of sliced eggs and spread remaining mixture over eggs.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Melt Velveeta and stir in Ro-Tel and soup.
In a large baking dish, layer Doritos and hamburger meat.
Stir and place in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion.	Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and water (as if to make tacos).	Then add green chilies and black olives.
Set aside.
Mix cornbread mix, milk, eggs and corn.
In 13 x 9 greased or sprayed pan, layer 1/2 cornbread mix and all meat; top with cheese.
Spoon on rest of cornbread mix. Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, adding salt and teaspoon of oil.
Drain.
Grate cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk and pepper.

title: frozen sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread.
Don't allow to rise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear one loaf and drop helter skelter into pan.
Melt butter and add rest of ingredients to butter and beat until smooth.
Tear second loaf and put in empty spaces.
Let rise until even with top of pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: no fail cherry cobbler
directions: Heat can of cherries.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Melt margarine or butter in 2 quart baking dish.
Pour the mixed batter over the top of the melted butter, then pour hot fruit over batter and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: extra dark fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa; mix well.
Add water and milk; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Do not stir while cooking.
After reaching soft ball stage, put pan in cold water.
Add butter and vanilla.
Swirl butter until it melts.
Do not stir.
Let stand in cold water until warm.
Beat until glossy shine disappears.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: fancy fast chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top each piece with slice of cheese.
Arrange mushrooms over cheese. Mix together soup and wine; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: cheese and cream apple pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry and sprinkle bottom with flour and sugar.
Mix together.
Toss together apple slices, sugar, nutmeg and diced cheese.
Place in pastry-lined pan.
Pour cream over the filling.
Cover with lattice pastry top and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until well done and lightly brown.

title: danish apple cake
directions: Add eggs to sugar, then add flour.
Mix well and add butter, nuts, apples, salt and vanilla.
Put in greased and floured pan, about 9 x 12-inch, and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Saute the ground meat in a skillet.
Add the taco seasoning mix and the water per package instructions.
Pour 1/2 cup taco sauce into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1/2 of the tortillas on the bottom of the pan.
Spoon on all of the meat mixture.
Top with the sour cream in even "dollops." Sprinkle 1/2 of the cheese. Arrange the other 1/2 of the tortillas, overlapping slightly on the cheese.
Spread remaining taco sauce and top with rest of cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 5 more minutes.
Serves 8.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with lettuce, tomato and guacamole.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid into glass bowl or jar.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add beets, eggs and onions.
Cover.
Chill 2 hours or longer before serving.
Drain eggs and serve in one dish, onions and beets in another.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: In a bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and mix.
Meanwhile, cube up angel food cake (store bought; even day old from bakery works fine).

title: san antonio chili
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add all ingredients except the cornmeal and bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for one hour.
Stir in cornmeal and uncover 3 minutes, stir occasionally.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together in pan over low heat. Cool slightly.
Place cooled chocolate mixture, eggs, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Blend about 1 minute.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add with nuts to first mixture.
Blend until all flour is mixed in.
Pour into greased loaf or bread pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut in squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: special k candy
directions: Bring to boil the first three ingredients.
Then add last three ingredients.
Mix cereal, peanut butter and nuts with sugar and corn syrup.
Roll in balls and place on waxed paper.

title: no-knead rye bread
directions: Combine milk, shortening, molasses or brown sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm by adding water. Add dry granular yeast dissolved as directed on package; mix well. Blend in egg. Add enriched flour and rye flour. Mix until dough is well blended. Cover and let stand for 15 minutes. Shape dough into a long loaf; place on a greased baking sheet and cover. Let rise in warm place (85-90 degrees) until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Brush with egg white diluted with 1 tbsp. water. With a sharp knife make three diagonal cuts across top of loaf. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: savory grilled pork chops
directions: Combine contents of gravy mix envelope, water, lemon juice, oil, catsup and soy sauce.
Arrange chops in shallow pan.
Pour gravy mixture over and let stand at least 30 minutes, turning occasionally.
Grill over hot coals or in broiler about 6 inches from heat for 20 to 30 minutes, turning frequently and brushing with gravy mixture.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat lemon cake mix, lemon instant pudding, 1/3 cup oil, 1 cup water and eggs with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and save liquid.
Melt butter and add onion.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add flour to mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk and stir until mixture bubbles.
Add broccoli and 1 cup saved liquid.
Season with salt, pepper and lemon juice. Puree in blender.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Prepare bread for dressing.
Cook celery and onions in 1 cup water on low heat until tender.
Add to the crumbs and seasoning. Stir in beaten eggs and enough broth or milk to make a moist dressing.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until browned.
Or, stuff the crop and body cavity of bird.
The dressing will swell during roasting, so pack it loosely.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shoofly cupcakes
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar to fine crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbs for top.
Mix water, molasses and baking soda.
Add to remaining crumbs and beat until very thin batter.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or fill cupcake tins 1/2 full.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350°.
Cake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cupcakes 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken
breasts, bone and cut into small pieces. Save broth.
Cover 9 x 13-inch pan bottom with chicken.
Cover chicken with noodles.
Mix together and pour over noodles the soup.
Mix a
box
of
Stove Top stuffing as directed.
Break bread
into stuffing
mix.
Spoon this over the soup mixture. Bake
for
one hour
at 350° covered.
Take cover off last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Place flour, meal, salt, pepper and paprika into a paper bag.
Shake several times to mix. Place 2 pieces at a time in bag so that chicken is well coated. Put melted butter in baking dish large enough for chicken to lie flat.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn chicken several times during baking to assure browning.
Serves 4.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix apples with 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon.
Spoon into a deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with 1/2 cup flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Add nuts and sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: copper pennies for 50(yields 50 servings)
directions: Bring salted water to boil.
Add carrots.
Boil ten to twenty minutes.
Drain and add to sauce while hot.
Marinate overnight.

title: rokki's cookies(nutty white chunk cookies)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
In a large bowl, blend sugars.
Add butter until creamed.
Add eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour mixture, nuts and chocolate.
Blend just until mixed; do not overmix!
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes in a 300° oven.
Transfer while hot to a cool surface.

title: homemade boursin cheese
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll into a ball and cover with lemon pepper.
Chill well.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients and stir until moist. Do not over stir!
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: potato beef casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Transfer to a greased 2 qt. baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 - 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: tater tot recipe
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients
in
an oblong baking dish. Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake
at
300° for 1 hour or higher degree for less time.

title: hirvonen sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat together with onion and pepper.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients to pan.
Simmer until mixture thickens.
Serve on buns while hot with a slice of cheese placed over mixture.

title: montana beans
directions: Cook onions with bacon until light brown.
Drain off fat.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and garlic salt.
Cook with bacon and onions for 20 minutes on stove.
Add all beans.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Can use foil.

title: graham bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add graham flour to thicken. Make a stiff batter.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Fills about 5 cans.

title: polish sauerkraut and kielbasa
directions: Open and squeeze juice from sauerkraut.
In a large roaster, layer sauerkraut, cabbage and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with peppercorn, bay leaves, caraway seed (and gin).
Break kielbasa (do not cut) into 2-inch pieces and arrange over top.
Cover and bake in slow oven (250° to 275°) for 4 to 6 hours.
This dish can be prepared ahead and is even better the second day.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened (about 15 minutes).
Add egg yolks and cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Fill pie shell.

title: peach caramel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread peaches in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange bread in single layer over peaches.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown beef. Drain and rinse with hot water. Combine all ingredients except chips and cheese in a Dutch oven. Simmer on low until done, about 45 minutes. To serve, crumble chips in a serving bowl. Cover with a good helping of stew. Sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix
cabbage,
water chestnuts and onion together.
Mix melted butter,
cream
of
celery
soup,	milk and mayonnaise together. In a buttered dish, add vegetables and pour mixture over
the top.
Sprinkle
grated
cheese over mixture and top with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: christy's cholesterol pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add the vanilla and chocolate and beat.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes between each egg.
Pour into crust and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: soft white sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add baking powder in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll on floured board and cut with cutter. Bake quickly in hot oven at 400° to 450°, sometimes 375°.
Makes lots of cookies and can use part and place remaining in refrigerator.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon and drain on paper towel. Cook and stir beef pieces, onions and garlic in bacon fat in Dutch oven until beef is brown. Stir in broth, water, barley, paprika, salt, caraway seed and marjoram. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 3 hours at 325°.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix with wooden spoon until damp.
Work quickly and lightly, as should not be over mixed.
Roll between sheets of waxed paper. Peel off top paper and flip over into pie pan.
This makes one large shell.
Can double or triple if desired.

title: cookie dough for filled cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar, white sugar and two eggs.
Mix vanilla, baking powder, soda and salt with 1 cup flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add 1/2 cup milk alternately with enough flour to make a soft dough.
Approximately 4 more cups flour.
Make into 2 balls and refrigerate overnight.

title: stefado
directions: Heat butter in heavy skillet with a good lid.
Season meat with salt and pepper; add to butter and coat; do not brown.
Add sliced onions on top of meat, then sliced carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat, onions and carrots.
Cover kettle and simmer for 3 hours; do not stir.

title: bruschetta with tomatoes and mozzarella
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place bread on a cookie sheet and toast
for 10 minutes (5 minutes on each side).
Rub both sides with garlic.
Arrange Mozzarella slices on each piece of bread. Heat
in
oven for 5 minutes.
Place a tomato slice on each
piece of bread; drizzle olive oil over each and sprinkle with basil, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: apple dumpling sauce
directions: Mix and boil.
Pour over dumplings and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: With level measure, sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make a hole in center.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares to serve and top with chocolate sauce.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cool and pour over fruit.

title: basic biscuit mixture
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
When you are ready to bake, combine 3/4 cup milk with 2 cups of dry mixture.
Bake in hot oven, 400°.

title: banana nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add Eagle Brand milk, salt and vanilla. Beat and add bananas and nuts.
Pour into ice cream freezer. Finish filling with milk.
Turn on freezer.
Yummy!

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix into batter and put into a greased pan.
Spread 1 quart of cherries over top, then sprinkle 1 1/2 cups sugar over them.
Add 1 quart boiling water on top and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: After
the raisins are soft, add the other ingredients. Mix and
cook
until
thickened.
Stir constantly.
Pour into baked 8-inch
pie
shell and top with egg white meringue made with
2 egg
whites,
teaspoon
salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
and 4
tablespoons sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pork roast
directions: Cover roast with mustard, then brown sugar.
Bake in oven until topping is brown; remove from oven.
Flame bourbon; pour over roast.
Cut up onions and apples; place around roast.
Pour 1 cup beef bouillon over apples and onions.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes per pound.
When done, add cream to juices, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Pour over meat to serve.

title: creative croutons
directions: Using a small cookie or canape cutter or a knife, cut desired shapes from bread slices.

title: fresh cobbler(peach, apple, blackberry)
directions: Sweeten and cook fruit.
Melt butter in pan.
Mix other ingredients together and pour into melted butter.
Add hot fruit. Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: home a la model
directions: Combine husband and wife to make a home.
Add children, one at a time (though some have excellent results, adding double or even triple).
Add more love and patience with each child.
Season with humor.
Saturate with tenderness.
Let ingredients settle in a warm atmosphere.
Garnish with memories, shared experiences, family fun, high hopes and cherished dreams.
If done slowly, carefully and under the guidance of Our Lord, this recipe never fails.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine cereal, milk and 1 cup of the tomato sauce.
Add ground meat and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put mixture into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Invert onto warm serving platter.
Heat 3/4 cup tomato sauce and spoon over meat.

title: torte cake
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, water and vanilla; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: prissy's guacamole beef rolls
directions: Mash avocado.
Add lime juice, onion, salt, chili powder, coriander, Tabasco and tomato.
Combine thoroughly.
Spread on slices of cold roast beef, allowing about 2 teaspoons for each slice.
Roll slices; wrap and chill.

title: magic peanut butter middle cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda. Blend well. In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar, margarine and 1/4 c. peanut butter until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and egg and beat well.
Stir in flour mixture until blended; set aside. In small bowl, combine 3/4 c. peanut butter and 3/4 c. powdered sugar; blend well.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
For each cookie, shape dough around each peanut butter ball.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet (ungreased). Flatten with hand. Bake at 375° for 7-9 minutes.
Decorate as desired.

title: mexicorn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef with green pepper. Drain well.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in soup and milk.

title: country style apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
After cake is done, pierce top with fork and glaze.

title: dynamites
directions: Simmer tomatoes, paste and garlic.
In separate pot cook oil, green peppers, onions, red peppers and celery (all chopped) until vegetables are soft.
Add sauce to vegetables.
Add hamburg last and simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: fluffy chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from broth and debone.
While you are deboning chicken, add soup to your broth.
Bring to a rolling boil and add flour tortillas by strips.
Add chicken last and let simmer.
Best when eaten with cornbread!

title: chicken cheese
directions: Open crescent rolls; pat out these lightly.
Place chicken pieces on crescent rolls.
Roll up and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk, soup and cheese together.
Pour over chicken rolls.
Bake covered 45 minutes at

title: lemon dessert
directions: Chill can of evaporated milk overnight.
Dissolve lemon juice in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water.
Add juice and rind of lemons and sugar.
Chill.
Whip milk until thick; blend into jello mixture.
Pour into glass baking dish (13 x 9-inch). Top with vanilla cookie crumbs; chill several hours.

title: cranberry-orange punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and water.
Boil 5 minutes. Cool and mix remainder of juice.
Chill thoroughly and serve.
Serves 20.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If soupy, bake longer.
This is also good reheated.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: oven roasted chicken
directions: Remove giblets and neck from chicken and reserve for other uses.
Rinse chicken with cold water.
Pat dry.
Combine herbs and seasonings and rub on surface and in cavity of chicken.
Lift wing tips up and over back so that they are tucked under chicken securely.
Place chicken breast side up in a shallow roasting pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Brush chicken with oil and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until done.
Chicken is done when legs move freely.
Let stand 20 minutes before cutting.

title: chili noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and mango.
Add remaining ingredients (except the cheese).
Place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with the shredded cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° or until cheese has melted.
Enjoy!

title: guacamole no. 1
directions: Process avocados in food processor until smooth.
In bowl, stir remaining ingredients into avocados.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin. Blend in sugar, salt and spices. Add milk; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: instant lemon bread(cake)
directions: Mix first
6 ingredients together. Pour into 2 loaf pans, sprayed with Pam. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil and cool the first 4 ingredients. Mix the next 2 separately. Mix the last 4; adding the first 4 ingredients, then add the flour & sugar mixture. Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool 1/2 way & frost.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar and water.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.

title: three week homemade wine
directions: Place in a gallon jug (such as apple cider jug, etc.); put a balloon on top and set in warm place for three weeks.
Strain several times through layers of cheesecloth and then bottle.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and add rest of ingredients.
Let chill at least 2 hours before serving.
It is best when it is made a day before and left standing in refrigerator overnight.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix all together; let rise until double.
Put in pans; let rise until double.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
After baking, brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour water over oats and add margarine.
Let stand 10 minutes. Add sugars and mix.
Add eggs.
In separate bowl, sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa together.
Add to first mixture.
Add 1/2 chocolate chips.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pimento cheese(makes 45 sandwiches)
directions: Grate cheese.
Mash pimentos with fork.
Mix cheese and pimentos well.
For a
creamier
filling add heated evaporated milk until you
reach the desired texture.	Makes 45 sandwiches.

title: aunt chrissy's blueberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, salt, cornstarch, lemon, margarine and 1 cup blueberries until thick.
Place remaining blueberries in shell.
Pour mixture over berries and refrigerate 2 hours or more.

title: mexican salad
directions: Layer, in order listed, all ingredients on a plate.
Repeat layer of lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Again, repeat layer of lettuce and tomatoes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: linda poor's barbecue ribs
directions: Bake ribs in water in a 350° oven for 90 minutes in a covered pan.
Drain and cover the ribs with the barbecue sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Pour over pickles and onions.
No need to heat anything.
Cover and let stand for 5 days in refrigerator.
Pickles may be stored in the refrigerator for up to a year.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter. Add ground beef and cook until brown and crumbly. Parboil for a few minutes. Add potatoes, carrots and spaghetti to meat mixture. Add 1 cup shredded cheese, cream chicken soup with 1 can milk, salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle top with shredded cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious cake
directions: Mix
well
and bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture, then stir in cherries, raisins and pecans.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop with teaspoon about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: crock-pot artichoke dip
directions: Heat through in crock-pot on high for 1 hour or less. (Watch so it doesn't stick.) Serve with tortilla chips or potato chips.

title: surprise congealed salad
directions: Cook pineapple and Jell-O until Jell-O dissolves completely. After mixture cools completely, add remaining ingredients.
Place mixture in jel-ring or jel-n-serve and store in the refrigerator at least 4 hours before unmolding.

title: taco layered dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Dip with nachos or any corn chips.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add green chili peppers, drained and chopped, with all remaining liquids.
Place small amount of liquids on bottom of casserole.
Line casserole with tortillas.
Layer meat, cheese, sauce and tortillas until casserole is filled.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground turkey or beef, combined with the chopped onion, bouillon cube, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Drain all grease (if any).
Spray 3-quart casserole dish with Pam and put mixture in dish, stirring in shredded carrots. Prepare potato flakes according to directions on package.
Spread potatoes on top of meat mixture.
Bake until potatoes are brown on top.

title: shrimp and oyster gumbo
directions: Heat oil in
a heavy saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat; add flour very slowly, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until flour
is
very brown.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is
soft but not brown.
Add tomatoes, fish stock, shrimp and bay leaves; simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Add seafood seasonings; simmer 45 minutes.
Add okra, salt and pepper; continue to
simmer 5 minutes.
Add oysters and simmer 10 minutes or	until
edges of oysters curl. Just before serving, stir in gumbo file.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Dip chicken in oil.
Roll in mixture made from the first seven ingredients.
Drizzle remaining oil very lightly on top of chicken.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Put pears and vegetables through a food chopper. Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and allspice.
Pour into an enameled pot with chopped ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Pack in hot, sterile jars.

title: fantastic fruit bars
directions: *Suggested combinations: orange jello with apricots and orange rind; lemon jello with prunes and lemon rind or peach jello with mixed fruits (omit rind).

title: cream of parsley soup
directions: Bring
chicken	stock to a boil, add parsley and simmer 30 minutes.
In a bowl beat the egg yolks and lightly beat in heavy cream.
Add
to chicken soup gradually; stir until soup thickens slightly, about 5 minutes, do not boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: seasoned roast beef sandwiches
directions: Place roast in roaster pan.
Cover top of roast with onion and celery.
Pour teriyaki sauce over top.
Bake 6 hours in covered roaster at 250°.
When done, shred meat with a fork and mix well. Serve on buns.
(This tastes better the next day, so you can make it ahead of time and just reheat.)

title: gourmet spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain thoroughly.
Stir sour cream and onion soup into spinach.
Put in greased casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.
Can be made in advance.

title: finger paints
directions: Combine starch and 3/4 cup cold water in pan.
Soak gelatin in the remaining 1/4 cup water.
Add hot water to starch mixture and cook over medium heat until mixture boils clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; blend in softened gelatin.
Add soap and stir until soap is dissolved.
Cool.
Divide into screw-top baby jars and add desired coloring.

title: apple pudding
directions: Slice apples into greased casserole.
Mix well the following: flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and well beaten egg until crumbly.
Dot apples with sugar, cinnamon and butter; then cover with crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until top is brown and crusty.

title: fudge nut orange bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, oats and margarine at low speed until fine crumbs form.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for filling.
To remaining crumbs, blend in 1 egg until well mixed.
Press in bottom of prepared pan.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and spread on cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with the chocolate pieces while it is still hot.
Spread chocolate that is melted and sprinkle with the nuts on top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: brown sugar sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat chocolate with water in saucepan over very low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks; add vanilla.
Beat egg whites in large mixing bowl until foamy throughout.
Gradually beat in sugar until stiff peaks form, about 3 minutes.
Stir a small amount into chocolate mixture to lighten; fold chocolate mixture into remaining whites.
Pour 4 cups into a buttered 9-inch pie plate sprinkled with sugar.
Chill remaining mixture.

title: pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in flour, oil, sugar and 1 teaspoon of salt. Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Let rest 5 minutes.

title: double baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and pierce in several places.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes until done.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and let stand until cool enough to handle.
Scoop out inside, leaving skin intact.
Mash potatoes with oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon mixture into potato shells and sprinkle tops with parsley and paprika.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes until tops are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli until tender; drain broccoli.
Saute onion in margarine.
Put broccoli and onion with margarine, soup, milk and Cheez Whiz into crock-pot.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Delicious with hot cornbread.

title: kyles red beans and rice
directions: Cook rice and keep warm. In saucepan heat oil, add celery, garlic, onion, thyme and cook until tender. Stir in beans, canadian bacon, chicken broth, worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce and cook. Sprinkle with remaining parsley when done.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Cream sugar, oil and butter together.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, then add buttermilk, coconut, flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and nuts.
Pour into 3 well-greased cake pans. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and ice.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into large bowl, mix 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 more minutes on high speed.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given in 10-inch Corning dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs dotted with butter.
Cook in 350° oven uncovered for 35 minutes.

title: five in one salad(ambrosia)
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator for at least 1 to 2 hours or overnight so all blend together nicely.
I use multicolored miniature marshmallows.

title: crab mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water and let stand 1 minute.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Blend in sour cream and dressing.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Mix jam, dressing, soup mix and water; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until brown. Serve with rice.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Shred zucchini; if very watery, drain well while preparing batter. In large mixer bowl, beat eggs. Add oil, sugar, molasses and vanilla; beat until thick and foamy. Combine flours, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon; add to egg mixture. Stir just until blended.

Add zucchini, raisins and nuts; mix gently to avoid crushing zucchini shreds. Divide batter between 2 greased and floured 5 x 8-inch loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven 1 hour. Allow to cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Keeps 2 weeks or longer in refrigerator.

title: cheesy meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Form into small balls.
Brown in pan or bake in 400° oven until brown.
Add meat balls to spaghetti sauce and cook slowly for 20 minutes until meat balls are done.
Makes 12 meat balls.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and chips.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all wet ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to batter.
Stir well.
Line 2 loaf pans with wax paper; spray ends with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
While still warm, pour over top glaze (powdered sugar and warm water).

title: aunt fannie's cabin baked squash
directions: Cut squash and boil until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except butter, to squash.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter.
Pour mixture into greased casserole and top with melted butter and additional cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, tuna and garden peas.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add onion and carrots; cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Remove from heat.
In large plastic food storage bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add beef; shake to coat.
Add coated beef and any remaining flour mixture to vegetables.
Cook over medium-high heat until beef is browned.
Stir in broth, wine, water, bouquet garni, parsley flakes and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Stir in mushrooms and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes or until mixture thickens and mushrooms are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Blend together all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: animal friendly oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine oats, sugars, flour and salt.
Combine soda and hot water.
Stir into oats mixture.
Add shortening and vanilla to oats mixture.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden.

title: candy corn
directions: With a parent helping, cook the frozen corn according to package directions.

title: chicken bake
directions: Combine soups and mix well.
Arrange chicken in baking dish. Salt and pepper chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: pudding pound cake
directions: Dice up pound cake to cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Sprinkle small can of drained crushed pineapple over this.
Mix instant vanilla pudding according to directions on package and pour over cake and pineapple.
When set, top with coconut and Cool Whip.

title: olive garden style fettucine alfredo
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a sauce pan and heat over low heat, stirring frequently, until melted and creamy.
Add salt and garlic.
Serve over pasta.

title: yum yum
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine (melted) and pecans.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until brown.
Cool completely.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Saute celery and onions in bacon grease or margarine until celery is transparent but not brown. Crush crackers.
Add celery and onions.
Add the eggs and mix together.
Stuff fish.
Pour tomato sauce over fish.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes easily with fork.
Good with just about any fish.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Let stand overnight; drain in the morning.
Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits.
Make pies by placing applesauce or cooked apples on 1/2 of biscuit.
Turn other 1/2 of biscuit over apples; seal with fork tines dipped in flour.
Place pies in large greased baking pan.
Bring to boil 1 cup water, the margarine, sugar, nutmeg and allspice; pour over pies.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until brown.
Spoon syrup over pies.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate bark and almond bark in microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Stir until melted.
Put back in for 45 seconds on High. Stir again.
Add peanuts.
Drop by spoonful onto wax or foil paper.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain excess fat.
Prepare vegetables.

Layer refried beans in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Heat beans in microwave or oven just until warmed thoroughly. Layer 1/4 cup of cheese, layer of ground beef, layer of sour cream, layer of lettuce, tomato, onion and remaining cheese on top.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: eggplant a la parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange eggplant in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch aluminum pan or Pyrex dish.
Top with onion, then tomatoes. Drizzle 1/2 cup margarine over entire casserole.
Sprinkle with basil and garlic salt.
Cover and bake for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Toss crumbs with 1/4 cup melted margarine and spread over casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: thousand island salad dressing
directions: If too thick, add a small amount of milk.

title: best oatmeal bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 3 cups flour, oats, sugar, yeast and salt.
In saucepan, heat water, milk and margarine until warm (120°to 130°).
Add to flour mixture until well moistened; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Lightly grease large bowl; put dough onto lightly floured surface and knead 5 to 8 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Shape into a ball and place into greased bowl, turning once.
Cover and let rise in warm place 30 minutes or until double in size.
Grease two 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Punch dough down, cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Shape into 2 loaves and place in pans.
Brush lightly with melted butter.
Sprinkle with oats, if desired.
Cover and let rise until nearly double in size.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until dark golden brown.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well and drop with spoon onto wax paper.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda together.
Cream sugar and Miracle Whip and alternately put water and flour mixture in while beating.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit medley punch
directions: In blender, puree strawberries.
In punch bowl, combine strawberries and remaining ingredients except ginger ale; stir until sugar dissolves.
Before serving add ginger ale and ice ring.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Cut celery stalks into 2 to 3-inch pieces and boil until tender.
Drain. Dip each piece in seasoned beaten egg and flour. Fry in olive oil until golden brown. What a tasty side dish for any meal!

title: bourbon balls
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler over hot water; remove from heat and stir in sugar, syrup and bourbon.
Combine wafer crumbs and nuts.
Stir in chocolate mixture; blend well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional ground nuts, powdered sugar or coconut.
