Store airtight for 1 to 2 weeks before serving.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Combine beef and onion in a skillet; saute until browned.
Combine beef mixture and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yield 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; whip together with berries until creamy and smooth.
Chill overnight to set and develop flavor.
This is a good sandwich filling, fruit salad topper, toast spread or cake frosting.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In medium size heavy saucepan over low heat, melt the margarine.
Add the carrot, onion, potato, garlic, bay leaf and thyme, tossing to coat the vegetables with the margarine.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the chicken broth.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes or until almost all the liquid has evaporated.

Raise the heat to moderate, stirring in the remaining 2 cups chicken broth and the milk and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are very tender and the flavors well blended, about 30 minutes.
Cool the mixture slightly and strain it, reserving both the vegetables and the liquid.
Discard the bay leaf.
Place the strained vegetables and 1 cup of the broth in a food processor or electric blender and puree by whirling for 1 minute.
Return the puree and reserved liquid to the saucepan.
Add the salt and pepper and bring to serving temperature over moderate heat, about 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: miss grace's greens
directions: Wash and pick through greens.
Put water and fatback in large boiler pan and boil about 5 minutes.
Add greens and salt.
Add sugar to take out bitterness.
Cook until tender.

title: watermelon jam
directions: Remove seeds and cut watermelon meat into cubes.
Place in preserving kettle with sugar.
Add orange and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring very often to prevent mixture from burning.
Cook jam until it will stay in place when dropped from a teaspoon onto a cool plate.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: hamburger delmonico steaks
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a bowl.
Form into large flat steaks about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Broil on both sides 3 inches from heat source until desired rareness.
Serve topped with fried onions if desired.
Serves 2.

title: bean pot beef stew
directions: Place beef in a 4-quart bean pot or casserole dish.
Add flour over meat with fork.
Add the soup mix, cubes, salt, pepper and sauces.
Fill bean pot 2/3 full of boiling water.
Stir and add carrots, potatoes and celery.
Cover and bake in 275° to 300° oven for 3 hours.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a hard boil the sugar, cocoa (or peanut butter), oleo and milk, then add oats and vanilla.
Mix and drop on wax paper. Let stay to set.
Yields about 2 dozen cookies.

title: frost me not chocolate cupcakes
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
butter
together.
Stir in butter flavoring.	In a bowl slightly beat the eggs.
In another bowl mix sugar
and	flour.	Add
the
eggs, flour and sugar to the chocolate-butter
mixture.	Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
These freeze well.
Makes 20.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, place chicken.
Cover with cold water; season to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Bring back to a boil to cook dumplings.

title: grandma's coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg; mix well. Add vanilla. Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture.
Add coconut and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: frozen cappuccino
directions: In small saucepan, bring 2 cups of water and the sugar to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in instant Espresso powder, hazelnut extract, cinnamon and vanilla. Stir in evaporated skimmed milk. Transfer mixture to 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover with foil and freeze until ice begins to form around the edge of the pan, about 2 hours. Spoon mixture into large bowl.

Using electric mixer on medium speed, beat until light and fluffy, 4 to 6 minutes. Divide mixture into 4 freezer-safe dessert dishes. Cover with foil and freeze until firm, at least one hour or overnight. To serve, remove foil and let stand in refrigerator for 10 to 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter casserole dish.
Lay 1/3 of tomato slices on bottom.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and 1/4 of the cheese.
Repeat with remaining slices.
Top with 1/2 cup of cheese and dot with butter.
Bake, covered, 40 to 60 minutes. Brown under broiler if desired.
This is a simple way to use green tomatoes and it tastes great.

title: mock pecan pie(oatmeal pie)
directions: Mix all ingredients, leaving oatmeal last.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato family pie
directions: Spread 1 cup sugar in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut margarine and spread over sugar.
Add dash of salt and vanilla. Add 1/2 of the sweet potatoes and place strips of dough lengthwise over them.
Add remaining potatoes; cover with remaining sugar. Cover with strips of dough.
Pour water over pie and bake at 375° until crust browns.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook until potatoes are done.
Remove from oven; spoon syrup over crust.

title: southern barbecue chicken(farm journal cookbook, circa 1959)
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Wash well and pat dry.
Put giblets to stew in 1 quart salted water.
(Will use this broth in barbecue sauce to follow).
Put flour, salt and pepper into paper bag.
Shake chicken in flour, a few pieces at a time.
Saute chicken pieces until golden brown on both sides in hot shortening in heavy skillets.
Arrange pieces in open roasting pans.
Add giblets.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.
(No harm in baking chicken a little longer, the flavor actually improves).
Makes 50 servings.

title: chili rice
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and 10 ounces of cheese.
Place in casserole and top with additional 10 ounces of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Lightly flour chicken and brown in oil.
Put in baking dish, cover with Swiss cheese.
Add soup to oil to make gravy and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or after browning chicken, leave in skillet and pour over soup and cover skillet. Cook slowly until chicken is done.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: strawberry soda
directions: Put sliced strawberries, 1 cup ice cream and 1/3 cream soda in blender.
Blend 30 seconds. Divide among 3 tall chilled glasses. Put a scoop of ice cream in each glass.
Pour in enough cream soda to cover.
Garnish with whipped cream and whole strawberry.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine all salad ingredients.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Grease inside
of
quart casserole with butter. Crumble raw meat into casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice and onion soup mix
and water together in small bowl.
Pour rice mixture over meat.	Cover
tightly	with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan. Stir and boil until all the water cooks out. Pour onto a cookie sheet and separate until cool.

title: oriental cashew crunch(quaker oats)
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.
Combine remaining 4 ingredients in small bowl; quickly pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 10 cups.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions.
Let cool; stir in other ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chocolate explosion
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package in two 9-inch round cake pans.
Let cool.

Place one 9-inch round cake in the bottom of a large deep container (I use the top of my Tupperware cake carrier or large salad bar container), then pile on enough chocolate pudding to cover top of cake, then a layer of Cool Whip and a handful of candy. Repeat process using second 9-inch round cake pan (cake, pudding, Cool Whip and candy).
This recipe is simple, but delicious and goes quickly at parties.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking soda, cocoa and salt; set aside.
Meanwhile in small saucepan heat butter and water on low heat until butter is melted. Beat eggs, buttermilk, and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Add flour mixture, mixing well.
Pour in butter and water from saucepan and mix well once again.
Pour into greased and floured 15-inch by 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Spread chocolate frosting over cake.

title: butter buds
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 and next 4 ingredients. Mix well and add walnuts.
Roll into small balls.
Press cherry on top or walnut.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Holiday cookie.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the brown sugar, butter, sugar, eggs and peanut butter.

title: betty's spice cake
directions: Combine sugar, molasses, buttermilk, butter, flour, baking soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add the two eggs last.
Mix well. Bake at 350° until cake springs back.

title: margarita pie(pastel de margarita)
directions: Mix
graham
cracker
crumbs, sugar and butter together and press into	a
9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: quick 'n easy cioppino(fish soup)
directions: Saute onion, garlic and pepper in olive oil until soft, about 10 minutes.
Add liquid from clams, tomatoes (chopped), tomato sauce, wine, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano, basil and water. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add seafood; return to boil.
Simmer an additional 20 minutes.

title: chip bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients in the order given. Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, cut straight 2 inches wide lengthwise.
Cut diagonally across the width.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening.
Add vinegar, water and egg to flour.
Chill 15 minutes before rolling out.

title: savory chicken squares
directions: To prepare, blend cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth; add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup mix into center of each.
Pull 4 corners up and twist to seal.
Brush tops with butter.
Dip in crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: potato pancakes
directions: Soak potatoes in water for 10 minutes; drain and squeeze dry in a kitchen towel.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except the oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour a little oil into a large skillet.
Place over medium heat for each pancake.
Pour 1/2 cup potato mixture into the pan; flatten slightly.
Cook about 7 or 8 minutes, until crisp and brown.
Repeat with more oil and remaining potato mixture.
Serve with sour cream and applesauce, if desired.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Cream the cheese and add 1/4 cup cherry juice and 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of Cool Whip.
This is your dressing.
Add this to drained fruit and marshmallows.
May use lite cream cheese.

title: savory chuck steak
directions: With sharp knife, cut and discard fat and bones from chuck steak; cut meat into strips 1/4-inch wide.
In a large bowl, toss chuck with flour, salt and pepper.
In a large skillet over medium heat, in salad oil, brown steak.
In crock-pot or pan on stove, add onion soup mix, extra onions, 1 cup cold water, chili sauce and meat.
Heat on low for 2 hours. Serve garnished with parsley over bow tie noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 12 ounces chocolate chips and 1/2 stick margarine or butter and spread on top.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet, drain fat.
Stirring, bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Flip with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with lettuce, pickles and tomato slices.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix flour and water; add to onion mixture.
Add Cheez Whiz and melt.
Mix broccoli in mixture; add eggs.
Pour into greased pan and cover with bread crumbs.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and pour over crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chess cake(cookie)
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bake at 300° until done.
Cut into squares and serve as cookies.

title: 7-up salad(or burps for a bunch)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, add 7-Up.
Let set slightly, then add oranges, pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Let it jell before adding topping.

title: taco dip
directions: Take a Corning Ware dish or any dish that will cook in hot oven.
Spread refried beans on bottom.
Mix sour cream and the taco seasoning mix together, then spread over beans.
Add the cooked hamburger meat, then cover with the Cheddar cheese.
Add hot sauce, if desired.

title: cheese puff appetizer
directions: Roll out white bread.
Spread with Cheez Whiz.
Add asparagus spear.
Roll up in bread.
Brush with butter.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Bake in broiler until brown.

title: sausage-wild rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown sausage in skillet, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Combine rice, sausage and all other ingredients in large bowl.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Cook until syrup spins a long thread.
Pour gradually into 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add nuts and beat until it holds its shape.

title: lazy woman's pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix batter and pour in butter. Add fruit and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Cover buttered baking dish with croutons. Mix all ingredients, except onion rings, and put in baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. The last 15 minutes, put onion rings on top.

title: shrimp cantonese with rice
directions: Saute shrimp in oleo for 1 minute in a large skillet.
Add celery and onion, stirring for 2 minutes.
Add spinach and drained vegetables; add blended soy sauce, broth and cornstarch.
Cook 2 minutes until clear.
Serve on rice.

title: orange creamsicles
directions: Put 1 (11 ounce) can of mandarin orange segments in a dish (drain juice and save).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash and dry potatoes (works just as well for sweet potatoes). Coat each potato with Crisco oil.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12.

title: joe froggers
directions: Sift together flour, salt, ginger, cloves, nutmeg and allspice.
Combine rum and water.
Add soda to molasses. Thoroughly cream Crisco and sugar.
Add half the dry ingredients, half the water mixture, then half the molasses mixture.
Blend well after each addition.
Repeat.
Chill dough several hours. These cookies may be rolled out and cut into desired shapes or just shape with hand.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Watch carefully so they don't burn.
Reduce heat to 350° if cooking too fast.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook shredded cabbage until tender; drain thoroughly.
In large skillet saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in cabage and salt and pepper.
Transfer to ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
In small skillet melt remaining butter and add crushed Ritz crackers until lightly browned; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Excellent.

title: green beans with zucchini
directions: Remove strings from beans; wash beans thoroughly. Cut beans into 1 1/2 inch pieces. Wash thoroughly. Cook beans in boiling salted water 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp tender. Melt butter in a large skillet; add onion and saute about 3 minutes. Add zucchini and cook over medium high heat 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in beans, bacon, salt and pepper; cook 1 minute.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix in zucchini.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: holly candy
directions: Melt together butter and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and stir in cinnamon, vanilla and green food coloring.
Then add frosted flakes.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Then shape into either a wreath or a Christmas tree. Then decorate with red hot candies.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into well buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes, maybe less. Check and see if browned lightly and custard is set.
Enjoy!!

title: robin's potato stuffing
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Saute in butter the following ingredients separately:
bread (can cube first or do whole like grilled cheese sandwich), onion and parsley.
Mash potatoes and add milk until smooth.
Mix egg, onion, parsley and bread together with potatoes.
May want to add more milk if needed.
Can refrigerate overnight and heat in the morning.

title: chili recipe
directions: Brown beef in a small amount of oil. Add onions and garlic. Cook until soft. Add next 7 ingredients. Simmer for about 2 hours. Add oatmeal. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.

title: crescent chicken bundles
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onions and pimentos. Stir well.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli as indicated on packages.
Mix together all ingredients except Cheez Whiz.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.
Spread Cheez Whiz on top a few minutes before taking out of oven.

title: old time tea cakes
directions: Mix in order listed.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar (optional).
Bake at 350° until golden brown (12 to 13 minutes).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, apples, salt and butter; repeat layer.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° covered.
Cook uncovered 25 to 30 minutes more. Add cinnamon.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil and cool before adding the cream cheese, baby food and pineapple. Add the two mixtures well, then add the Cool Whip. Chill.

title: gypsy's meal
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, then fry them.
Cut ham in small pieces.
Cut cheese in strips.
Scramble the eggs.
Put ham and eggs in with potatoes over medium heat.
When eggs are done, add the cheese.
Turn off stove.
Feeds a family of 6.

title: mexican rice(with sour cream and green chile)
directions: Cook the rice in boiling salted water until just tender.
Cut each chile lengthwise into 3 strips.
Cut half the cheese into small oblongs, wrapping a chile strip around each piece.
Butter a casserole and put a layer of well-seasoned rice, then 2 or 3 stuffed chile peppers.
Season with salt and pepper, cover with sour cream, then repeat until all ingredients have been used.
The top should be of sour cream, the remaining cheese, grated and the butter in dots.
Put in a 350° oven until browned on top, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: saltine cracker candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and boil for 3 minutes.
Put single layer of crackers on cookie sheet.
Pour sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Spread chocolate chips over saltines while hot (so chips will melt).
Sprinkle almonds on top; refrigerate to cool.
Break into pieces.
Leftovers can be stored in refrigerator.

title: richard's talarinie
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Boil macaroni elbows; drain. In large pot, mix meat and macaroni.
Add drained corn, chopped olives and diced tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until bubbly.
Can be topped with grated cheese.

title: caramel dip
directions: Heat butter, brown sugar and milk.
Stir constantly.
Add vanilla, corn syrup and water.
Bring to a boil.
This is good for apples.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the night before and refrigerate.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.

title: sweet-sour pork for crock pot
directions: Place pork in crock pot. Add green pepper and onion. In bowl, mix brown sugar and cornstarch. Add 1 cup pineapple juice, vinegar, water, soy sauce and salt. Blend until smooth. Pour over meat and vegetables. Cover, cook on low 5-7 hours. One hour before serving, add pineapple chunks. Stir into meat and sauce. Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt fat in 2-quart saucepan.
Brown onion, green pepper and beef in hot fat.
Add tomatoes, soup, paprika, cayenne, bay leaf and chili powder.
Simmer about 1 hour, adding water if mixture gets too thick.

title: peppy rounds
directions: Brown meat and drain very well.
Add next ingredients and mix well until cheese melts.
Spread a tablespoon of mixture on party rye bread or Triscuits.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in plastic bags in the freezer.
Take desired amount from freezer and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet (with raised rim) with foil.
Place single layer of graham crackers on sheet, touching each other.
Melt the butter.
Add the sugar; boil for 2 minutes.
Sprinkle the chopped nuts on crackers.
Pour butter mixture over all.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
When cool, break apart.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: rarebit soup
directions: Mix soups, milk and water.
Heat and serve with croutons.

title: three-precious fried rice
directions: Heat the wok.
Add the oil.
When the oil is hot, add the salt and stir in the shrimp, pork, onion and celery.
Stir vigorously until the onion is just transparent.
Stir in the pimento, just to mix, then add the eggs, stirring constantly.
Add the bean sprouts and peas.
Stir to mix well.
Stir in the rice; continue stirring until the rice is thoroughly mixed with the other ingredients. Add the soy sauce, a little at a time, stirring after each addition.
The soy sauce will give the rice a lovely light brown color.
(Add more soy sauce if it is not salty enough, but more than 6 tablespoons of soy sauce will make most rice too soggy.) Stir in the minced green onions.
Serve very hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Mix apples, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon. Place in a deep 8-inch baking dish. With a pastry blender, mix 1/2 cup flour, brown sugar and oil. Place over apples. Put a little cinnamon on top. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes until apples are done and it is brown and bubbly.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw dough; let it rise until doubled in bulk.

Divide in half. Roll out first half on a floured surface into a 10-inch circle. Combine egg and Parmesan cheese, stirring well; spread half of mixture over dough leaving about 1/2 inch margin around edges. Layer 3 1/2 ounces pepperoni, 1/2 cup Cheddar and 1/2 cup Mozzarella over egg mixture.
Roll up dough jelly roll style. Transfer loaf, seam side down, onto an ungreased baking sheet, making sure all seams are closed tightly.
Repeat procedure with other half of bread dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut into slices to serve.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cream 1/2 stick butter and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes, vanilla and milk.
Mix well with mixer.
Place in greased casserole dish. Mix brown sugar, pecans, flour and melted butter.
Crumble on top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Pour water in large bowl; add yeast and stir until dissolved. Add milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and half the flour.
Mix until smooth.

Add enough of remaining flour to handle easily. Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth; shape into ball, place in greased bowl, cover and let rise 1 hour in warm place. Punch down, let rise again about 30 minutes.
Shape into desired rolls and bake in usual manner.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Heat milk on low until it's warm; add chocolate powder and cocoa.
When dissolved, remove from heat.
Beat eggs and sugar together and add vanilla.
Pour mixture in a glass pan.
Cut bread into cubes and cut off crust.
Put the bread in the mixture evenly.
In another pan, add a little warm/hot water and put pan with the pudding in that pan.
Cook at 400° for 1 hour.
Let cool and serve with fresh whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix chopped apples and sugar and let stand 20 minutes.
Add to apple mix the flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Next add to apple mix the eggs, salad oil, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.

title: hanukkah potato latkes
directions: Scrub potatoes, but do not peel.
Coarsely shred potatoes and onions.

Mix shredded potatoes and onion with eggs, flour and salt in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat into 3 tablespoons hot salad oil; drop potato mixture by heaping tablespoons, pressing gently with pancake turner to flatten.
Cook latkes until golden brown on both sides; remove them to warm platter as they brown and add more salad oil to skillet as needed.
Makes about 16.

title: is it cabbage?
directions: Place cabbage in 4-quart casserole.
Pour milk over cabbage. Sprinkle crumbs over top; dot with margarine.
Bake covered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover; bake 20 to 30 minutes until crumbs brown.

title: rubber taffy
directions: Stir until dissolved and cook until 270° on candy thermometer (soft crack).
Pour into buttered, shallow pan and cool until it can be handled.

title: pumpkin layer cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to first 4 ingredients.
Mix on medium speed for 1 minute.
Ladle into 3 greased and floured pans and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out to completely cool before frosting.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Add sugar and flour to eggs.
Combine with pineapple.
Place in a baking dish and sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and crumble graham crackers over top.

title: chateau briand
directions: Preheat broiler to high.
Place meat, cut side down, on flat surface
covered with a clean cloth and pound with a flat mallet. Turn
meat over; cover with clean cloth and pound the second side. The
meat
at
this
point
should measure about 5-inches in diameter
and
1 1/2 to 2-inches thick.
Sprinkle meat on
both sides
with
salt and pepper to taste and brush with oil all over. Place meat on broiler rack and place under broiler so
that
the top
of
meat is only about 2-inches or slightly less from the source of the heat.
Broil 5 minutes on both sides.
Shift broiler
rack
to bottom of oven and broil another 5
minutes. Using
tongs,
transfer meat to a carving board and
wrap in heavy-duty foil to keep warm.
Let stand 15 minutes and serve with Bearnaise sauce.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, stir in peppers and onions. Pour 1/2 of batter into greased iron skillet and sprinkle half of cheese over batter. Pour in remaining batter and top with rest of cheese. Bake at 375° for 35 - 40 minutes. Check with cake tester.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Slice sausage and set aside.
Wash and cut vegetables. Stir-fry vegetables in a wok or skillet in 3/4 cup beef bouillon until crisp.
About 5 minutes before they are done, add in sliced sausage.
Serve over white rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Put in 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and Crisco together.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead as biscuits.
Cover, put in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: lemon madeleines
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Liberally brush Madeleine pan with some melted butter. Mix ingredients in order as shown and fill molds. Bake until lightly brown, approximately 15 minutes. Top will spring back when pressed. Cool in pan for 1 minute and then turn Madeleine's out on rack to cool completely. They should be crisp on the outside and light and fluffy on the inside. Store in airtight container. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: dijon almondine sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Serve on steak or roast beef.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: *Add after sugar mixture is removed from fire.

title: brazilian rice and beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight or by quick method.
Cook about 2 hours or until tender.
In saucepan, cook together the vegetables.
Saute remaining ingredients (except rice) together in a skillet.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Join beans, vegetables and meat mixture and heat together two minutes.
Serve with rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry banana shake
directions: In blender, combine ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Makes 2 (8 oz.) servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° to 450° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gingerbread upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 1/2 cup syrup.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Blend in 1/2 cup sugar.
Remove from heat.
Arrange pineapple in skillet.
Place cherry in center of each slice.
Cream remaining butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Combine remaining ingredients. Bring reserved pineapple syrup to a boil.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with hot syrup.
Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until cake tests done.
Cool in skillet 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: In a large bowl blend flour, sugar, cinnamon and soda.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil and remove from heat, oleo, cocoa and water.
Pour over dry ingredients and add eggs and
buttermilk. Beat together well.
Grease a large deep cookie sheet.
Pour batter in pan and top with nuts.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
As soon as you put cake in the oven, start icing.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown 1 1/2 pounds of sausage; butter a cake pan.
Put in stuffing.
Drain sausage; put sausage in 2 cups shredded sharp cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard; pour over cheese.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: peanut butter haystacks
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter.
Mix coconut, peanuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool.

title: grape-chicken salad
directions: Combine grapes, chicken, walnuts and celery.
Add combined dressing and ginger; mix lightly.
Chill.
For each serving, spoon mixture over cantaloupe.
Garnish with additional grapes.
Serves 4.

title: pork or chicken bake
directions: Put
meat
in
baking pan.
Slice tomatoes on top.
Add onion and
bell pepper.
Mix the rice with the 2 cans of soup. Pour this over the meat.
Bake at 400° until tender.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup, broth, chilies and pepper.
Set aside.
Mix chicken and onion together.
Put approximately 2 tablespoons chicken mixture in center of tortilla.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and roll up.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Continue until all tortillas are rolled.
Pour soup mixture over top of tortillas and sprinkle with remaining grated cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dough thin on bottom of round pizza pan or flat 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes; cool.
Stir together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch mix.
Spread onto baked dough. Top with veggies and cheese.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix together first 7 ingredients.
In small bowl, mix together apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Alternate layers of batter and apple mixture in pan.
Begin and end with batter.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: souper burgers
directions: Fry ground chuck and onion slowly until done.
Add soup, ketchup and mustard.
Simmer until hot.
Serve over toasted, buttered bread or buns.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, 15 minutes or longer.
Drain and mash.
Add butter and cream cheese.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and next 6 ingredients.

title: black bean dip
directions: Mix all together.
Salt and Pepper.
Let set for several hours.

title: hot chicken and dressing dish
directions: Saute celery and onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add soups and 1/2 cup chicken stock and chicken pieces.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole and set aside.
Combine stuffing 1 cup chicken stock and butter and spread on top of casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover first 15 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place in a big pan.
Heat and enjoy.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine soda and flour.
Starting with flour, alternate flour and sour cream into butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, keep the syrup and add enough water to make 1 cup. Dissolve jello in the boiling water and add the juice water. Add sherbet by the spoonfuls; stir to melt.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges (keep a few for top garnish).
Pour into serving bowl; chill and garnish.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: nut loaf(vegetarian main-dish)
directions: Saute in oil the onion, parsley, garlic and oregano.
Combine nuts, bread crumbs, ketchup, wheat germ and soy sauce. Put all ingredients together into a loaf shape. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve in place of meat loaf, sliced.

title: jelly roll
directions: Add ingredients in order listed. Place dough in shallow pan and bake at 375° until done. Turn out on a sugared cloth; spread with your favorite jelly and roll while still warm.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into thin slices but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish and fan slices slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10-15 minutes, or until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft when checked with a fork.

title: chow mein candy clusters
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces in heavy saucepan or in top of a double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in the noodles.
Coat all carefully.
Add the pecans and mix quickly.
Drop on wax paper with a teaspoon.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Melt caramels in milk (in microwave or on top of stove).
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in margarine or Crisco.
Add egg.
Press 1/2 to 1/3 mixture into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake crust at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Turn oven off.
Sprinkle chips and nuts on top. Drizzle caramel over chips and nuts.
Sprinkle remaining crust mixture over top of the caramel.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 40 minutes covered; remove from oven and add Topping ingredients.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar and 4 cups water together.
Bring to a boil and then cool.
Mix coffee and 1 cup boiling water; let cool.
Mix everything together and allow to sit in sealed containers for 3 to 4 months.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and cocoa together.
Then add sour milk and soda, mixed together, and mix thoroughly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: lickin good salad
directions: Mix jello and water until jello is dissolved.
Chill until it starts to gel.
Whip cream and mix with cream cheese.
Fold all ingredients into the partly jelled jello.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips well with the milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (2 to 3 hours).
Turn onto cutting board.
Peel off wax paper. Cut into squares.
Store at room temperature.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with warm crispy bread.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Stir butter to soften.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating smooth after each addition.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Apple Topping.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.
Cool 15 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam the zucchini and onions for 10 minutes. Fry sausage and drain.
Mix all of this with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, just until hot.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add ham, parsley, dry onion, dry mustard, Tabasco sauce and water.
When mixed, roll in pecans.
Chill.
Serve with flavored crackers such as Sociables.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix cheese, sausage and biscuits together. Roll into small balls (1-inch).
Preheat oven to 325°.
Place balls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: swedish rice porridge
directions: Boil water, salt, butter and cinnamon.
Add rice of the round-grained type.
Boil for approximately 10 minutes under a tightly fitting lid over low heat.
Add milk.
Let the rice boil for another 30 to 40 minutes over very low heat until milk is absorbed.
Stir now and then so that the porridge does not burn. Add approximately 1 tablespoon sugar to taste.
Serve with milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and soak in bowl of salted cold water (1 tablespoon in 1 quart water) for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix.
Add celery to 1/2 of dressing mix.
Put 1/2 of dressing mix in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with chicken.
Mix soups and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken and dressing mix.
Spread over half of dressing mix on top of this. Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover for the last 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs, flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, salt and bananas (optional raisins and walnuts).
Stir in by hand.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift all ingredients together.
Make 3 holes.
In the first, put 2 teaspoons of vinegar.
In the next, 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
In the third, 3/4 cup of salad oil. Pour 2 cups cold water over all and stir with a fork until well blended.
Pour into the pan and bake for 40 to 45 minutes, more or less, at 375°.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Cream the pudding, butter, sugars and vanilla together, then add eggs, flour, soda mix and chocolate chips; beat well.
These cookies are soft dough can be frozen for later.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook meat, if needed, then fry together with diced onion and green pepper until tender.
Add tomato sauce, pimento, bouillon and salt.
Bring to boil.
Add rice (rinse well).
Add water; bring to a boil.
Cover and cook slowly at low heat for 1/2 hour, or place in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water; add potatoes, onion and celery. Cook until tender.
Add frozen vegetables.
When tender, add soup. When warm, add cheese.
(Can use any vegetables you wish.)
Can do ahead and can freeze.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Break off leaves and drop in boiling water until limp; drain. Place meat in each loaf; roll and pin with a toothpick.
Flour, salt and pepper; brown on all sides in a skillet whole bottom has been covered with Crisco oil or butter (as desired).
Cover with tomato soup; then add enough water to cover all.
Cover and simmer until done.
Enjoy!

title: beef patties with cheese
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and shape into 6 patties.
Place in buttered baking pan and dot with oleo. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes, basting twice with drippings from pan. Cut cheese slices into halves.
Place a strip on each patty and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: popover pizza
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in
a
large
skillet
until meat is browned, stirring to crumble
meat;
drain.
Add sauce mix, tomato sauce and water, stirring
well.
Simmer
minutes. Spoon meat mixture into a lightly
greased
9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: italian delight
directions: Fry the lean ground beef.
Cut up onion and bell pepper into small pieces and add to ground beef; fry until tender, stirring well.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, chili pepper and creamed corn. Cook the noodles.
Mix noodles with meat mixture.
Put in greased baking dish. Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Bake.

title: delta kappa gamma punch
directions: Add sugar to water and heat until sugar dissolves.
Mix with other ingredients and freeze until needed.
Before using, let thaw 2 to 3 hours to form slush.
Put in punch bowl and add 2 to 3 bottles of ginger ale.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, onion and cheese in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream, green chiles and Jack cheese.
Fill flour tortillas with chicken mixture and place in greased casserole dish.
Spread soup mixture over top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(It seems to always take more time and if prepared early in the day, it'll take longer to heat through).
They freeze well.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add sugar and flour to yeast mix.
Blend.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Cover with greased wax paper (even if using Tupperware).
Put in refrigerator.
After chilling, make rolls as needed.
Brush melted butter on rolls in greased pan. Use lots of melted butter in pan that is warm.
Rise in warm place, approximately 2 hours.
Bake in 350° to 375° until desired color. Keep unused dough in refrigerator.

title: pattye's sopa de tortilla con pollo y arroz
directions: Cook rice according to box directions and let sit, covered, until ready to use.
Saute onion until tender in 2 tablespoons of oil in a Dutch oven.
Add chicken cubes and cook until no longer pink.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over chicken.
Add rice, chicken and rice soup, tomatoes with green chilies and chicken broth. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: pork chop and potato dinner
directions: Grease baking dish and arrange chops in bottom.
Put layer of potatoes and onions on top.
Salt and pepper.
Add soup and water. Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat together mashed potatoes, dip, sour cream and cream cheese; season to taste and place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika for color and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, until heated through.
Cheese may be grated on the top and melted also.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature.
Mix all (except pecans) and shape into a ball.
Chill and roll in chopped pecans.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces. Save 1/2 cup of broth.
Combine soups, milk and broth.
Cook until just heated.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half of mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top of stuffing mixture and pour soups over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onions, tomatoes and seasoning.
Put into a layer about 1-inch thick in a baking dish or pan.
Add rest of ingredients in layers, in order as listed, ending with cheese or bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Beat well and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup, together. Form into small balls. Brown in hot fat. Cover with undiluted cream of chicken soup. Cover. Bake in 300° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix well with soup.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Add onion rings.
Then return to oven and heat onion rings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, put layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding, layer of crackers, pudding, crackers, then ice with can of milk chocolate icing.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Mix together.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Don't toss early.
Toss just before serving!

title: roasted red pepper and corn chowder
directions: *Rub red pepper with olive oil and roast whole in 400° oven for about 40 minutes, turning to ensure that all skin becomes blackened.
When black, place in paper bag and let cool.
When cool, skin peels off easily.
Remove seeds and membranes and finely chop.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses and mix well.
Add flour and salt, sifted together, and mix well.
Add baking soda to boiling water and immediately pour into batter and mix well.
Pour into square 9-inch casserole, greased well, and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or when center of gingerbread springs back when pressed.

title: sparkling jewel dessert
directions: Using three separate bowls, dissolve raspberry, cherry and lime gelatins in boiling water, using 1 cup for each.
Stir 1/2 cup cold water into each gelatin.
Pour gelatins in 3 (8-inch) square baking pans.
Chill until set.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Put gelatine, sugar, water and pineapple in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil about 5 minutes.
Partially cool and add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a 9 or 10-inch square pan and chill for several hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Salt and pepper.
Add chili beef soup and tomatoes or tomato soup.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook elbow macaroni until tender.
Combine sauce and macaroni in a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Place in oven and heat until cheese melts.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry dough.
Prick the dough all over.
Bake for 16 to 18 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: shore stew
directions: Dredge meat with seasoned flour.
Brown meat in hot oil in 2 large cast-iron frying pans.
Add a large can of tomatoes to pan and simmer briefly.
Transfer to large containers suitable for oven baking.
Add sliced onions.
Add carrots, peeled and cut into large chunks.
Add potatoes, peeled and cut into large chunks.
Add celery, cut into thick slices.
Add seasonings.
Add water to cover.
Bring to boiling on top of stove.
Transfer containers to ovens, preheated to 200°.
Leave in ovens until serving time, at least 5 hours.

title: turkey salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and roll into 3 sticks, 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate 24 hours. Unwrap and place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in warm water for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix sugar, butter, eggs, water and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients and add to first mixture, blending thoroughly.
Fold in apricots and nuts.
Pour into three 1 pound pans that have been greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine
peanut
butter with confectioners sugar, cream cheese and
whipped
topping.
Spoon
mixture
into
crust. Combine chocolate
chips with milk, butter and sugar over low heat.
Stir until all is melted, then spread over pie.	Serve chilled.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 cup coconut, water, egg whites, Dream Whip (dry, not made up) and coconut extract.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hometown special cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Add applesauce and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients well.
Gradually add to mixture, beating well each time.
Add raisins and nuts.

title: chicken or turkey enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in margarine or butter until tender.
Add water, taco seasoning, and poultry.
Mix and cook on med. heat until liquid is cooked out.
Fill wraps with meat mixture, and roll into enchiladas.
Place in greased baking dish.
Mix milk and cream soup.
Pour over top of enchiladas.
Top with cheese, can be made ahead and frozen before baking.
Bake 350° until cheese is melted and hot throughout.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix ham, cheese and onions together.
Put into center of crescent roll triangle.
Put ends of triangle up and close.
Beat egg and brush each roll with egg mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add onion, egg and buttermilk. Beat well.
Fry in deep fat. (Especially good if fried where fish has been fried.)
Drop into fat by small spoonfuls.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sausage.
Beat eggs.
(I add onion salt, Parmesan cheese and a little milk.)
Pour over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Let set for 24 hours.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in blender and mix.

title: loie's favorite tater soup
directions: Chop potatoes, carrots, celery, onion and smoked sausage as desired.
Cover with enough water in pan to cook.
Brown hamburger and drain.
When vegetables are done, add hamburger, 1/2 stick butter and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil. Thicken with flour and water.
A very hearty soup.
Just ask Loie, it sure is good!!

title: a love cake for mother
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a hearty, warm oven; serve to Mother everyday.
She should have it in big slices.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix with pastry blender or fork and knife until pea size, then add 4 to 5 tablespoons cold water.
Cover and chill 1 hour, then roll out.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes.

title: green beans in herb sauce
directions: Cover.
Cook over moderate-low heat until tender (5 to 10 minutes).
Season.

title: sweet 'n sour beans
directions: Fry bacon and cook onion in bacon grease.
Combine all ingredients; crumble bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish coffee
directions: Pour whiskey into 8 ounce microproof mug or cup. Add coffee and sugar. Add water to fill 3/4 full; blend well. Place in microwave and cook on high, (100%), for 2 minutes. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Top with dollop of whipped cream. Do not stir. Coffee should be sipped through the layer of cream. Enjoy.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let pies set in oven for 10 minutes after oven is cut off.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup, eggs, cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Mix.
Put in casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried woodchuck
directions: Cut woodchuck into serving size pieces.
Boil in salted water for 1 hour.
Remove and roll in salt and peppered flour.
Fry in oil until browned.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup mixture in 4 cups water until done.
After adding cabbage and tomatoes, salt and pepper when vegetables are cooked. Add okra and ketchup.
Cook on slow.
Boil for about 30 minutes.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: *Can substitute 3 to 5 cups granola cereal for All Bran and 40% Bran.

title: beef rolls
directions: Cut meat in 8 rectangular pieces.
Spread mustard on meat. Sprinkle with onion.
Top with half strips of bacon and with pickle strips.
Roll up like jelly roll, tucking in edges. Tie with cord or skewer securely.
Coat rolls with seasoned flour and brown slowly on all sides in hot oil.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Stir together.
Cover and refrigerate.
Delicious with carrot sticks, celery, cauliflower, broccoli, etc.

title: banana tea loaf
directions: Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt into mixing bowl. Into blender container put eggs, butter, bananas and sugar.
Cover and blend on high speed for 20 seconds.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix just to combine.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir into beaten egg yolks (reserve whites for meringue) and return to heat.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
Then add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with coconut meringue.

title: sweet sour slaw(6 servings)
directions: Place shredded cabbage in a covered bowl in the refrigerator for several hours.
Thirty minutes before serving, mix ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Chill.

title: sweet and sour smoky links
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and dry mustard.
Add vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil and boil one minute.
Add Smoky Links and pineapple chunks.
Simmer one hour or longer!

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: Mix cookies with butter.
Press in bottom of pie server. Spread ice cream over top of cookies.
Pour fudge topping in even layer over ice cream.
Spread whipped topping over fudge.
Garnish with chocolate curls or cookies.
Freeze 2 hours.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Melt butter. Crumble crackers into small crumbs.
Pour mixed ingredients into 9-inch casserole dish.
Spread crumbs onto top.
Evenly pour melted butter on top of crumbs.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes until top is brown.

title: braised apples
directions: In a bowl, toss apples, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
In a non-stick skillet, heat butter and oil over medium heat.
Add the apples and saute for 1 minute.
Pour in cider, cover, reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir in ginger.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine
pineapple
and
water.
Heat
and add gelatin. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add other ingredients. Stir well and chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick and easy - praline grahams
directions: Separate each graham cracker into four sections and arrange in a jellyroll pan with edges of crackers touching.
Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in sugar and pecans or nuts of your choice; bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes, stirring almost constantly.
Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool on wax paper.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Blend in milk and shortening.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While hot, cut into squares and invert each onto dessert plate, spooning sauce over each serving.
May be served as is, or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Mix oil with dry ingredients.
Add eggs.
Add persimmon pulp mixture. Mix in nuts, dates and raisins.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients all together; form into balls.
Put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with marinara sauce.

title: navajo stew
directions: Put in large pot and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with chopped onions and grated cheese.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt. Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour all into square glass casserole dish and place in freezer until firm.

title: quick apple pies
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Add 1 tablespoon applesauce.
Add cinnamon.
Cover and use fork to seal edges.
Fry in hot grease until brown.

title: stuffed "ripe" tomatoes
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion and green pepper in skillet.
Cut off top of tomatoes and scoop out center seedy portion with a spoon.
Chop center portions.
Drain ground beef; add salt and chopped center portions.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add approximately 1 cup mayonnaise or to taste and heat through.
Fill tomato shells and serve.

title: chicken swiss crisscross
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate 1 can of dough into 2 long rectangles.
Press over bottom and 1/4 inch up sides of ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes, or until light golden brown.
In large bowl, combine chicken, broccoli, cheese, onion, mustard, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spoon chicken mixture over partially baked crust.

title: chicken l'orange
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces; season with salt and pepper. Dredge with flour.
Heat oil in skillet; add chicken and brown lightly on all sides.
Remove chicken to 3-quart casserole.
Drain fat from pan.
To skillet, add remaining ingredients, except orange slices.
Simmer 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken in casserole.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Just before serving, garnish with oranges.

title: oatmeal health muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Fill muffin tins and bake at 420° for about 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and pour into well-greased and lightly floured iron skillet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrot sticks
directions: Peel
and
cut	carrots
in 3-inch sticks and precook 5 minutes;
drain
and cut in thin sticks.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water and mustard seed.
Tie cinnamon and cloves in cloth bag. Add
to sugar, vinegar and water mixture.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Pour over carrots.	Refrigerate overnight or 8 hours before serving.
Drain before serving.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples and cut into halves (8 pieces).
Wrap each piece in a crescent roll and place in a greased baking dish. In a saucepan, boil orange juice, butter and sugar for about 1 minute.
Pour over crescent rolls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 40 or 45 minutes, or until brown on top.

title: okra casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Mix with 1 pint water, 1 can of hot tomatoes and peppers, 1 garlic button, rice, bell pepper and okra.
Sprinkle with black pepper, parsley and oregano.
Bake in casserole pan in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks lightly.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix in the butter.
Stir in the milk.
Add cooked rice and raisins.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Pour into greased pan; bake in a 450° oven until light brown.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and combine with sugar, salt, vanilla and scalded milk. Mix well and pour into pie crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake in a 350° oven 35 to 45 minutes or until mixture does not stick to knife.

title: rigatoni and sausage:  sicilian-style
directions: In a medium size skillet, cook the sausage with the green pepper and onion.
When sausage is cooked completely through and the vegetables are tender; drain.
Stir in the spaghetti sauce, your own or bottled sauce.
Add the sugar and the fennel.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: tomato meat loaf for 50
directions: Mix together beef and pork.
Add rest of ingredients and mix by hand.
Do not overmix.
Spread evenly in long baking pan. Divide into two loaves, firming to shape.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Slice each loaf into 25 servings.

title: crab mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in water and add to heated soup.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Mold; serve with crackers.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of water from the 2 cups.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl; add flour.
Knead until soft dough forms.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Set bowl in a warm place and let it raise 3 to 4 hours.

title: beefy rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a meat loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: veggie sauce
directions: Whisk mayonnaise and sugar; stir in soy sauce and parsley. Serve over any cooked vegetables, especially broccoli or green beans.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt with beater and put in a greased casserole dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add enough juices to sugar & cream cheese that you have drained from the fruits
to make it creamy. Add all other ingredients, add Cool Whip last.
Fold in well and put in refrigerator.
This makes a huge bowl of fruit salad.

title: black bean casserole(low-fat vegetarian)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and tortillas, in large pan and heat to boiling to combine flavors.
Layer 6 of tortillas in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon 1/2 of bean mixture and 1/2 of cheese and alternate again, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with sour cream for topping.

title: duck sauce(a country thanksgiving at the lamars)
directions: Bring Bing cherries and sugar to a boil.
Add mustard, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Add to ducks that have been baked, boned and shredded.
Serve with small biscuits.

title: baked beans
directions: Pick over beans and cover with cold water; soak overnight. Drain and then cover with fresh water.
Heat slowly, keeping water below boiling point.
Cook until skins will burst which is best determined by taking a few beans on top of spoon and blowing on them.
Skins will burst if sufficiently cooked.
Drain beans, scald pork and scrape.
Remove a 1/4-inch slice and put in bottom of bean pot.
Mix salt, molasses and sugar.
Add 1 cup boiling water and pour over beans.
Cover bean pot and bake 6 to 8 hours at 250°.
Uncover last hour and add boiling water, if needed.

title: blackberry dream dessert
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir until thickened.
Fold in whip cream.
Place half of angel food cake in bottom of 2 1/2-quart souffle dish or casserole dish.
Top with half of sweetened condensed milk mixture and 1 3/4 cup of blackberries.
Repeat layers ending with remaining 1/4 cup blackberries.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Yield: 10 servings.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese until fluffy.
Fold in milk until smooth. Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell. Chill 3 hours.
Serve with cherry pie filling (optional).

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown meat in skillet, adding salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot and add onion or onion flakes.
Cover with tomato juice (crock-pot must be at least 1/2 full).
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or longer for a large roast.

title: tofu creole
directions: Saute sliced celery with leaves on, chopped onion and chopped sweet pepper for 5 minutes in vegetable oil.
Add tofu, minced garlic and mushrooms and cook 2 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer until done, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: beef (or chicken) rice fiesta
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, brown the beef (or chicken) until done. Drain off fat. Add the butter or margarine with the Rice-A-Roni and onion to the meat and brown the Rice-A-Roni. Slowly add the hot water, pepper, tomatoes and chili powder (or cumin).
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle top with grated cheese and allow cheese to melt.

title: potato fluff
directions: Drain hamburger and add creamed corn.
Mix together.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and spread out.
Mash boiled potatoes and spread on meat mixture.
Sprinkle top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts, about 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mash potatoes; add rest of ingredients and mix well. Do not put marshmallows on at this time. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. During last 10 minutes of baking time, sprinkle marshmallows on top.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a loaf pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: Allow cream cheese and margarine to soften in a bowl, then cream together.
Add flour.
Roll onto well floured surface.
Cut into 1-inch biscuits.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: kiddie feast
directions: Mix pork and beans, mustard, ketchup, barbecue sauce and honey together in baking pan.
Cut sausage in small rings; add to bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: divinity
directions: Stir together sugar, syrup, water and salt. Boil to 240°. Slowly pour 1/3 of mixture over 4 stiffly beaten egg whites. Beat constantly. Cook remaining mixture to 265°. Beat the remaining mixture into egg whites. Cool. Add 1 tablespoon powdered sugar to spread crystallization. Then beat again. Add vanilla and pecans. Spoon up on wax paper. (Tape paper with scotch tape to counter top.)

title: baked ziti
directions: Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
In large saucepan, cook ziti and drain.
In medium saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons butter. Gradually stir in flour; cook over low heat 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add salt, mustard and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses and stir until melted.
Add ziti.
Pour into casserole.

title: lo-cal chocolate angel food cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and 3/4 cup sugar together 3 times, set aside.

title: beet jelly
directions: Measure beet juice and put in large saucepan.
Add ReaLemon and pectin.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and gelatin (jello) and boil for 6 minutes.
Ladle into sterile jars and seal.
Makes 8 1/2 pints.

title: diabetic banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas on crust.
Drain the pineapple and spread on top of bananas.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of pie.
Make pudding mixture as directions and pour over pineapple.
Sprinkle crushed nuts on top and refrigerate.

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined eggs, milk and margarine.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: mashed potato pancakes
directions: Add egg yolks to mashed potatoes in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk, baking powder and flour.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add beaten egg whites to batter. Fry on lightly greased griddle.

title: okra delight
directions: Cook okra and onion covered in skillet with oil until done. Brown ground meat in skillet.
Drain.
Add to okra.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients together. Make well in dry ingredients and add wet ingredients.
Add nuts. Pour into greased 9x5x3 baking dish.
Shield ends with foil. Microwave on med for 8 minutes.
Rotate dish and cook on high for 3-4 minutes.
(After 2 minutes on high remove foil.)
Let stand 5-10 minutes before removing from dish.

title: chocolate bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add eggs, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and buttermilk. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger (may add optional mushrooms); set aside.
Mix enchilada sauce and sour cream; heat.
Spread refried beans on tortillas.
On each one of tortillas, spoon on some hamburger; put some grated cheese on hamburger.
Roll up and place in pan.
When all are rolled up and pan is full, pour enchilada sauce over them. Top with cheese and bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mash cream cheese and mix with enough cole slaw dressing for consistency you want for a spread or dip.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Can be frozen.

title: nancy's mint cookies
directions: Oven: 375°.
Beat butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and peppermint extracts.
Mix well.
Spoon flour in lightly.
Add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Slightly flatten tops.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Leave on cookie sheet for 1 minute.
Remove and cool.
Spread chocolate icing on cookie tops.
Cut Andes mints into triangles.
Garnish cookie tops with mint triangles.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place 1 garlic clove and 1 pepper in each hot, sterilized jar. Pack firmly with clean young okra from which only part of the stem has been removed. Bring water, salt, and vinegar to a boil; simmer 5 minutes. Pour boiling hot solution over okra. Seal immediately. This will make 7 to 8 pints of pickled okra.

title: low-fat pumpkin mousse
directions: Make pudding and then mix all other ingredients.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add flour, salt and egg yolks and mix well.
Stir in evaporated milk and vanilla. Pour into pie shells and sprinkle each with 1 cup of chopped pecans.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° for at least 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes in jackets until almost done; chill. (Can use baked potatoes.)
Peel and grate potatoes.
Heat butter and soup; blend in sour cream, cheese and onions.
Stir in potatoes. Put in a casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients, sugar and mustard and heat together.
Cook carrots until just tender.
Mix onion rings and pepper strips with sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: turkey scaloppine with raspberry vinegar
directions: Flatten the turkey breasts and lightly dust with the seasoned flour, shaking off any excess.
(A powdered sugar shaker makes an excellent flour shaker for dusting.)
In a large nonstick skillet, heat the oil and saute the turkey over high heat, about 1 minute on each side, or until lightly browned.
Do not crowd the pan and do not overcook the turkey.
As the scaloppine is browned, remove to a warm platter.
Add the vinegar and then broth.
Bring to a boil and continue to stir until the sauce is smooth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour over the turkey and serve immediately, garnished with freshly chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and mashed bananas. Add dry ingredients.
Add milk and vanilla and mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup nuts, if desired.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until mixture dropped in cold water turns brittle.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten whites of eggs.
Add nuts and flavoring.
Then spoon on wax paper.

title: baked beans waikiki
directions: Cut pineapple into chunks, reserving 3 or 4 rings for garnish. Saute green pepper, onion and pineapple in margarine. Simmer 5 minutes. Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, catsup and brown sugar.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour pork and beans into baking dish. Add pineapple mixture. Stir gently to blend.
Place halved rings on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with chow mein noodles, if desired.
Serves 6 generously.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce and m.s.g. together until thoroughly blended. Add 1/2 cup pecans and 1/4 cup parsley.
Shape the mixture into a ball.
Place in a bowl lined with waxed paper or foil and chill overnight.
About 1 hour before serving, roll the ball in a mixture of the remaining pecans and parsley.
Place on patter and surround with crisp crackers.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Beat the eggs. Add sugar and oil. Beat together.
Add flour, baking soda and salt alternately with buttermilk.
Mix in bran cereal.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 10 minutes or so for fresh batter; up to 20 minutes for refrigerator batter. Store unused batter in covered container for up to 6 weeks. Do not freeze.
Makes 3 dozen muffins.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Roll and divide into squares and place quartered apples in each.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon. Wet edges of dough and pinch together.
Make syrup of sugar, water and butter.
Pour over dumplings and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown.

title: snacking cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1/2 cup of shredded cheese until well blended.
Bake at 475° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Remove from oven; top with remaining cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: whipped cream pineapple cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake according to package directions. While cake bakes, combine pineapple with juice and sugar in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often until thick and syrupy (20 minutes or so).

title: baked green rice
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo. Boil 4 cups of water and dissolve bouillon cubes in water. Mix vegetables, rice and hot water with bouillon cubes. Put in covered dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gloreo cookies(oreo cookies)
directions: Blend all ingredients together until you can shape the dough into a smooth ball.
Let stand 20 minutes, loosely covered.
Form dough into marble size balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten each with a smooth bottom of a drinking glass greased once and dipped into Nestle Quik powder.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and roll into balls. Place in 9 x 13-inch or 8 x 8-inch pan. Make the sauce from the remaining 4 ingredients and pour over the meatballs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions; drain in cold water and hold.
Combine all other ingredients and spoon into shells.
Spoon spaghetti sauce on bottom of pan.
Place in shells, open edge down, and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion rings in large serving bowl.
Prepare mixture of remaining ingredients. Pour over carrots, etc.
Better if refrigerated for 10 to 12 hours.
Will keep several days refrigerated.

title: crawfish stew
directions: Use an iron pot if possible.
Heat cooking oil.
Add flour and brown to a dark brown over a low fire.
Be certain to keep stirring this mixture constantly.
Add chopped vegetables; simmer over low heat about 1 hour.
Season crawfish tails with salt, black pepper and red pepper and add to sauce mixture.
Cover and continue to simmer over low heat for about 1 more hour.
Serve over rice.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Bring to boil red hots, sugar and water.
Cook slowly until candies are dissolved.
Core, pare and slice apples.
Put apples in hot syrup.
Cook slowly until apples are tender.
Serve warm.

title: spring breeze cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, sour cream, vanilla and whipped topping!
Pour into pie crust, chill, add fruit and serve.

title: brisket and beer
directions: Rub brisket with salt, pepper and garlic.
Place in roasting pan.
Cover with onion slices, celery, chili sauce and catsup. Cook, uncovered, at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add beer, cover and bake about 2 hours longer (until tender).
Cool.
Lift fat, drain and dispose of onion and celery.
Slice meat.
Cover with sauce and warm.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add vinegar and pineapple juice which has been pressed and drained from pineapple.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Cook until thick like salad dressing; stir continually. Let partly cool.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Grate cheese.
Layer cheese, layer dressing, layer marshmallows and layer pineapple. Do this until all is used.
May top with cheese.
Good topped with whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: chicken chilies casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix as package directs.
Brown chicken, chilies, celery and onion in large skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat until chicken and other flavors combine.
Add soy sauce and mushrooms. Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to sauce, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Place rice in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Place chicken-chilies mixture on top.
Serve.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together. Set aside. Pour fruit in bottom of 8 x 8 pan and pour melted butter over fruit. Then spread the sugar mixture over the fruit. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shirley's caesar salad
directions: Dressing:
In a jar, shake together first 6 ingredients. Chill overnight.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Split cake into 3 layers.
Mix other ingredients together and spread between layers.

title: paradise cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook pineapple and sugar until thick.
Spread on hot cake.
Cool completely. Slice bananas and spread over pineapple.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Spread over pineapple.
Spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut and pecans on top of cake.
Cool before serving. Keep refrigerated.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Place 1/2 of rolls on bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix hamburger, spices and sauce together.
Spread over rolls. Sprinkle with cheeses and mushrooms.
Cover with rest of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, milk and seasoned salt.
Add meat to egg mixture.
Stir in cheese and onion.
I use half and half for the milk for company.
Pour into greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until set and top is golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry short cake
directions: Tear angel food cake in small pieces and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Jell-O as directed; mix frozen strawberries and pour over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic cloves, sugar, salt and pepper. Slowly boil 1/2 box of lasagna noodles until tender.
