Drain and rinse with cold water.
Layer lasagna pan with sauce and noodles and sprinkle all three cheeses.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat juice until boiling.
Dissolve gelatin and jello in juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.
You may want to add chopped vegetables or seafood.
It's good!

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream the shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning with flour and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in blueberries. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix one melted stick margarine and 2 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Beat with mixer for 15 minutes, eggs, 2 sticks softened margarine and powdered sugar.
When well beaten, spread over crumbs in dish.
Cover this with sliced bananas.
Spread well with drained pineapple; spread Cool Whip over this.
Then add nuts and cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight and slice and serve the next day.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except potato chips.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cut together and set aside.

title: ice cream
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thickened.
Add 1 cup sugar and egg yolks, cool.
Add vanilla, egg whites, half and half and milk.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan.
Beat egg yolks and milk; stir into dry ingredients.
Cook at medium heat.
Stir constantly until thickened; remove from heat and add vanilla. Place wafers in a 4-quart baking dish.
Slice 3 bananas over wafers.
Add half of your filling; repeat the rest of pudding, bananas and wafers.

title: inside-out peanut butter cookie cups
directions: Place brown sugar, peanut butter, Crisco, milk and vanilla in a bowl.
Beat at medium until well blended.
Add egg; beat just until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; beat at low just until blended.
Refrigerate about 1 hour or until firm.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In a 4-quart dish, place brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, water and salt.
Microwave at High 12 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Add soda.
Pour over popped corn and peanuts.
Toss. Spread on foil to cool or form into balls.

title: dee's potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes. Combine with margarine, salt, pepper, onion, green pepper, sour cream soup and cheese.
Blend together with the potatoes and put in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix the cornflakes and melted margarine together and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.
This can be baked and frozen, then reheated to serve.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter well 9-inch pie plate.
Mix together sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla; set aside.

title: crab puffs
directions: Drain crab and flake.
Combine crab with onions, cheese, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Combine water, butter and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add flour and beat until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in crab mixture.
Drop batter by small teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 10 more minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mamaw's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate marble cream cheese pie
directions: For crust:
Combine 1 1/2 cups chocolate cookie crumbs, 2 tablespoons granulated sugar and 6 tablespoons melted butter. Press mixture into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes and cool.

title: scalloped cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook onion until wilted in butter.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 or more minutes, or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with chopped parsley, or a few dashes of thyme or other dried herbs.
Excellent for "potluck" meals.

title: lilias upton's prize winning english toffee
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup of the almonds.
Boil approximately 7 minutes to 289°.
Line cookie sheet (15 x 12-inch) with wax paper and spread toffee on the cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips and spread over the top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup finely chopped walnuts.
Press walnuts in the wax paper if necessary. When cool, turn toffee over and repeat process with additional 1 cup chocolate chips and another 1/2 cup of finely chopped walnuts.

title: ruby's easy potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes just long enough so potatoes are easy to peel.
Peel potatoes.
Slice into half or quarter pieces.
Season with Morton Nature's Seasons.
Bake in oven at 450° until brown.

title: great mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of round pan.
Then spread sour cream on top followed by salsa.
Layer the lettuce, tomatoes, and cheese on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Great party appetizer!

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs, bananas and dates.
Sift together the dry ingredients, then mix all together.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: slow cooker stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers and set aside.
Remove seed and membranes inside; rinse and drain.
Brown ground beef, drain and discard grease.
Combine onions, celery, rice, egg, salt, pepper and chili powder with ground beef.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Replace tops on peppers and place in slow cooker.
Combine soup and water and pour over peppers.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours on high setting.

title: cheese shortbread
directions: Cut cheese into shreds and cream with butter.
Sift in flour, salt and pepper.
Work this mixture into cheese and butter.
The mixture will be crumbly.
Press it together in a piece of waxed paper and chill for several hours.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness, folding crumbs over and over until dough holds together in an even rectangle.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 20 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely. Spread favorite cream cheese frosting between layers.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bone.
Saute onion and celery in butter. In large bowl, combine sauteed vegetables, broth, soup and Veg-All.
Stir until smooth.
Place in pie crust.
Put in chicken. Add liquid over chicken.
Top with pie crust.
Bake at 375° until crust is golden brown (about 40 to 45 minutes).

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix sour cream and dressing.
Toss together with vegetables in large bowl.
Garnish before serving with bacon bits (optional).

title: caesar salad
directions: Pour peanut oil into jar.
Add crushed garlic and let stand at least 1 hour.
Using 1/4 cup oil, saute bread cubes until golden brown.
Tear romaine, Boston and watercress into large salad bowl. Sprinkle with cheese, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Mix 3/4 cup oil, lemon juice, eggs and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over lettuce and croutons.
Toss lightly until well coated.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix in a large punch bowl and serve cold.

title: indian fried bread
directions: Enough water to make a medium stiff dough.
Mix together. Make a ball about 3 inches in diameter and pull the ball into a 6-inch circle with fingers.
Slash sides with sharp knife in about 4 to 5 places.
Heat one inch oil in skillet and when hot, drop in the bread.
Brown on each side and drain. Serve hot with meal or use honey or powdered sugar for dessert.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine and press onto bottom of casserole dish or deep dish pie pan.

title: lutheran brotherhood potato salad
directions: (Also can be added:
1/2 cup celery, 5 hard-cooked eggs, 1/4 cup onions and 1/4 cup carrots.)
We always add the onions and usually more than it says.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare rotini as directed on package; drain.
Cool pasta. Chop ham, salami, cheese, green pepper, onion, tomato and pickles. Combine into one large bowl.
Finally, pour Italian dressing over entire bowl.
Mix well; add salt and pepper to taste.

title: vegetable crescent
directions: Let cream cheese set to warm temperature; soften.
Spread flat crescent rolls in ungreased pan.
Bake.
Cool on wire rack.

title: chocolate tortoni
directions: Fold egg white mixture into whipped cream mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Put in Pyrex dish and freeze for 45 minutes.
Add chocolate chips; mix well and then add nuts.
Place mixture into paper muffin tins and freeze.
Makes approximately 7.

title: hot baked clam dip
directions: Using a sharp knife, cut top from bread and set aside. Hollow out loaf, leaving 1 1/2 to 2 inch thick shell. Cut removed bread in cubes and set aside. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in clams with reserved liquid, onion, beer, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, hot pepper sauce and salt. On a baking sheet, crisscross 2 sheets of aluminum foil, each long enough to cover bread. Center bread shell on foil and fill with clam mixture. Cover with bread top and wrap loaf with foil. Bake in preheated 250° oven 3 hours. Transfer loaf to large serving platter. Arrange toasted bread cubes and raw vegetables around loaf. Remove bread top and garnish dip with parsley. When empty, bread shell may be torn apart and eaten and it usually is! Makes 15 servings.

title: olive spread
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until it's soft. Mash with a fork and add the mayonnaise.
After this is mixed, add pecans and chopped olives.
Mix in olive juice.
Stir well.
This will be mushy, but it's supposed to be.
Put this in a pint jar or other container.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
It will become thick.
A delicious spread.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in skillet.
Slice margarine into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Add 1 can beef consomme. Sprinkle with rice.
Arrange pork chops over top.
Add remaining 1 can consomme.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: all-butter pound cake
directions: Let butter soften.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour (1/2 cup at a time), mix well and add flavoring.
Bake in a tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix together first four ingredients with fork or pastry blender.
Set aside.
Stir together egg, vinegar and enough water to make 1 cup.
Add to flour mixture.
Chill 15 minutes, or shape into balls; flatten and freeze.
Thaw and roll out for pie crust. Mixture may be stored in refrigerator for 3 weeks.
Makes 7 crusts.

title: coconut pumpkin custard
directions: Mix pumpkin sauce, brown sugar, salt and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and coconut.
Bring milk to a boil and add last.
Put in greased baking dish.
Set dish in a skillet of boiling water and bake at 350° until done.
To test, take a knife and cut in custard; if knife comes out clean, custard is done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sorghum molasses pie
directions: Just mix everything and heat up.
Then bake in moderate oven.

title: toffee
directions: Butter a square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Spread pecans in pan. Heat brown sugar and butter to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Immediately spread evenly over pecans.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Cover pan with cookie sheet.
Let stand approximately 1 minute or until chocolate chips soften.
Spread softened chocolate evenly.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Brown meat in oil.
Add cornstarch and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in tomatoes and water.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring frequently.
Place meat mixture and add remaining ingredients in foil pan.
Cover and bake for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir twice during baking.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add lemonade, undiluted.
Stir.
Add pineapple and banana.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: fruit soup
directions: Cook and boil until tender the prunes, apricots, raisins, lemon, sugar and water.
Add the tapioca, cinnamon and 1 cup of apples.
Cook.

title: blueberry belle crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spread in pie pan.
Combine next five ingredients. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over blueberry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix all together in a casserole (don't brown meat or onion first).
Bake about 2 hours at 325°.

title: five star salad
directions: Drain
all
fruits.
Mix
fruits with other ingredients and let stand at least 1 hour before serving.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: lo-cal dip
directions: Put cottage cheese in blender; puree until creamy smooth.
Add dressing mix; mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour, or until thickened.
Serve with veggies.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order.
Don't mix until you are ready to serve.

title: gazpacho
directions: Place the tomatoes, green pepper, cucumber and scallions in a bowl.
Make a dressing by combining the garlic, salt, pepper, lemon juice and oil in another bowl.
Add the parsley and basil and pour over the vegetables.
Chill for 2 hours.
Add the chicken broth and tomato juice just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain grease if necessary.
Add oregano, salt, pepper, soup and tomato sauce.
Turn down low to simmer.
Cook noodles as directed.
Drain and add to meat mixture or layer in casserole.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts but not browned.
Should be bubbly.
This freezes well, also.

title: health bread(three 1 pound loaves)
directions: Combine oatmeal, salt, shortening, raisins and boiling water in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, softened in lukewarm water, molasses, bran and whole wheat flour; beat vigorously.
Add white flour to form a soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place (82°) until double in bulk.
Mold three loaves; place in greased pans.
Let rise very lite.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in a lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When cake is cold, cover with Cool Whip.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake according to directions on box in rectangular pan.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. Mix confectioners sugar and cream cheese; fold in half of Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Mix pudding, milk and vanilla until thick. Spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate before serving.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter together in a pan in a 200° oven for 25 minutes. Let cool 3 or 4 minutes. Add Rice Krispies and miniature marshmallows. Add peanuts. Stir all together. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let cool in refrigerator for 4 or 5 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan drops
directions: Melt chocolate chips with Eagle Brand milk.
Throw in pecans. Drop on wax paper.
Let set out to dry.
Really yummy.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat oven at 350° and pour mixture into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, and paprika. Beat in honey, lemon juice, vinegar, & salt. Continue beating and slowly add oil. Stir in poppy seeds. Chill. Serve on fresh fruit or fresh raw spinach! Makes 2 cups.

title: cranberry salad 2
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Mix well.
When jello begins to thicken, add the cranberry sauce, bananas and pineapple.
Put in refrigerator to jell.
Spread sour cream (if desired) over the jelled mixture.

title: coffee punch
directions: Dissolve instant coffee in a cup of chocolate milk the day before making punch.
Ten minutes before serving, place chocolate milk, ice cream, almond flavoring and dollops of Cool Whip in bowl.
Stir and serve.
Delicious.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: In a crock-pot slice sausage (small).
Mix grape jelly with cranberry sauce. Pour over sliced kielbasa.
Turn on low for 8 hours. Can also be made in slow cooker; cook on low.

title: carol's coated peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together with hands.
Roll into balls or small rectangles.
Melt chips in top of double boiler.
Using 2 forks or tongs dip candy pieces into melted corals to coat.
Store in refrigerator.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Spray 9 x 11-inch baking dish with Pam. Line pan with jalapeno peppers. Grate Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese. Place on top of peppers. Mix together eggs, evaporated milk and flour. Pour over cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: toasted s'more bars
directions: Place 9 grahams in bottom of a 9-inch baking pan. Top with 36 marshmallow halves. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Top with remaining grahams. Arrange 4 marshmallow halves, cut side down, on top of each graham square. Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed and golden. Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into 18 bars with greased knife. Serve immediately.

title: snacks
directions: Beat eggs until thick and foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla and soft butter beating until creamy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into eggs.
Mix until mixture is a smooth batter.

title: nutty rice
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, marjoram, Tabasco and thyme; mix well.
Add rice, tomatoes, scallions, pecans and parsley.
Toss well to coat evenly.
Chill.
Garnish with tomato wedges and serve with additional Tabasco, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: piquant cocktail meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine beef, corn flake crumbs, parsley flakes, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and minced onion and blend well.
Form mixture into small meatballs about the size of walnuts.
Arrange meatballs in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.

title: aunt iris' hershey bar pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs. Heat all chocolate in microwave and melt. Add sifted flour, soda and salt into creamed mixture. Mix together in separate bowl, vanilla and sour cream. Combine all ingredients and pour into carefully sprayed/greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fried eggplant and onions with cheese sauce
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter, blend in flour and add liquids, stirring constantly while heating until sauce thickens.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Cover and keep hot over boiling water while preparing eggplant and onion.

title: darn good cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add cake mix, flour and egg.
Knead. Let rise to double it's size.
Knead.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick rectangle.
Melt butter and spread all over dough.
Add cinnamon and sugars and any optional items.
Roll dough as jelly roll.
Cut off slices and put in greased pan.
Set oven at 350°.
Set rolls to rise while oven is heating.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: fruitcake delicious(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Cut pineapple in bite size pieces.
Coat all fruit well with dry ingredients.
Beat eggs until frothy and add sugar gradually. Pour over fruit and mix well, coating each piece again.
Grease 2 bread pans well and line with wax paper, then grease wax paper. Pack mix good into corners of pan (leave no air pockets).
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: triple layer chocolate mousse cake
directions: In small bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water. Let stand 1 minute to soften. Add boiling water. Stir until gelatin is completely dissolved and mixture is clear. Cool slightly. In large cold mixer bowl, stir together sugar and cocoa. Add whipping cream and vanilla. Beat on medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bottom of bowl occasionally, until stiff. Pour in gelatin mixture and beat until well blended. Refrigerate about 1/2 hour.

title: hoppin' john
directions: In a large pot, place salt, pepper, red pepper and smoked neck bones.
Rinse peas.
Add to water.

title: crab pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on round dish for first layer.
Spread cocktail sauce for second layer.
Sprinkle crab meat on top.
Use crackers for dipping.

title: grilled potatoes and onions
directions: Arrange potatoes and onions on squares of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with butter, paprika, seasoned salt and pepper. Fold foil into packets and seal.
Place packets on medium-hot coals.
Cook, turning packets frequently until potatoes are tender, 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt.
Beat well.
Mix flour and soda; add to first mixture and beat well. Add chopped apples and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a tube pan or Bundt pan that has been greased and dusted with flour.

title: angel salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until lightly thickened.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple, celery, pimento and pecans.
Fold into gelatin and chill until thickened, but not firm.
Fold in whipped cream and chill until firm.

title: potato-peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sifted sugar into mashed potatoes, a little at a time, by hand.
Do not use an electric mixer.

Sprinkle waxed paper with additional confectioners sugar. Take ball of sugar-potato mixture about the size of a baseball. Roll out as for pastry and spread with crunchy peanut butter. Roll over and over like a jelly roll. Makes enough for two rolls, each about a foot long. Wrap in Saran Wrap or foil and chill well. Slice into 1/2-inch thick rounds.

title: peppermint hot chocolate
directions: Combine 1/2 cup hot milk with chocolate peppermint patties, stirring well.
Add pinch of salt and remaining hot milk.
Heat to simmering.
Do not boil.
Add cream.
Serve hot.

title: choose-a-chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Turn oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add shortening, egg, milk and vanilla; stir with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Stir in oats and "pieces."
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 10 minutes.
Cool on cooling rack.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and mix fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple and cherries. Add Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip, lemon juice, coconut and nuts. Mix all together and chill.

title: seafood salad 'n stuffing
directions: Combine ingredients and serve as a salad in tomato shells, green bell pepper, avocado halves or in pineapple, melon or papaya. Also ideal as filling for pita or pocket bread sandwiches.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in blender or mixer. Recipe can be doubled.

title: 30 minute bread
directions: Mix together and put in greased loaf pan after rolling in flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: west virginia pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
In double boiler heat milk.
Add sugar/chocolate mixture to milk until melted.
Stir constantly. Combine flour and salt.
Add gradually to milk.
Boil over low heat until beginning to thicken.
Cook additional 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into pre-bake 9 inch pie shell.
Top with meringue made with 3 egg whites and 4 Tbsp. sugar.
Bake until Browned.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and dip fresh fruit.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat shortening in skillet.
Add
onions and cook until soft. Add meat and cook
until crumbly.
Mix tomato paste and seasonings.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamed eggs
directions: Peel and chop eggs.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and seasoning; stir until well blended.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth.
Add eggs to hot sauce.
Serve on toast.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix together
the
first
ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion until translucent.
Add beef, juices and gravy. Add drained vegetables, mushrooms, herbs, thyme, basil, parsley, etc., and salt and pepper.
Taste for balance.
Add red wine; let simmer for a short time to marry flavors.
Place in a baking dish; let it cool.
Cover the top with seasoned mashed potatoes; instant are great for this.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: In a bowl, mix together cake mix and pie filling.
Pour in greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until tests done.
Cool and frost with a cream cheese frosting or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bananas in rum
directions: Boil the water, sugars and fruit until the syrup will glaze on a spoon.
Add the extract.
Slice the bananas and saute them in butter. Gently fold the bananas into the syrup.
Divide the fruit mix and syrup between 6 dessert cups. Sprinkle a teaspoon of rum over each serving.
This is best served hot.

title: spicy lentil soup
directions: In a kettle, cook the onions in the oil over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until they are softened.
Add garlic, celery and carrots and cook the vegetables, stirring occasionally for 10 to 15 minutes until they are softened.

title: chocolate chip bar
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Sift the flour, soda and salt. Add to the mixture.
Mix well. Add the vanilla and mix.
Add the chocolate chips.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 370° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add sugar, shortening, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat at medium speed. Add remaining flour. If sticky, add a little more flour.
Let rise.
Knead and let rise again. Make into rolls and let rise again. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 20 to 24 rolls.

title: fruit pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in pie shell at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: london sherbet
directions: Make syrup by boiling water and sugar for 10 minutes; pour over raisins.
Cool and add fruit syrup and nutmeg.
Freeze to a mush, then add wine and whites of eggs, beaten stiff, and continue freezing.
Serve in glasses.
Fruit syrup which has been left from canned peaches, pears or strawberries may be used.

title: hot pepper pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In 8 or 9-inch cake pan, combine pecans and melted butter.
Toast in oven 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add soy sauce, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Toss until coated.
Makes 2 cups.
Contains 209 calories per 1/4 cup.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, water and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook on High for 20 to 22 minutes or hard ball stage.
Stir once or twice while cooking.

title: apple quick bread
directions: *Five medium apples equal approximately 2 cups chopped.

title: chuck beef goulash
directions: Preheat 3-quart saucepan or 10-inch skillet.
Add cubes and brown on all sides about 10 minutes.
Add onion soup mix, tomato paste, mushrooms and water; cover.
When steam escapes from cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve over hot cooked egg noodles.

title: shrimp and orange chili salad
directions: Combine shrimp and mandarin sections, add chili flakes, salt, garlic and mint leaves.
Combine lime juice, fish sauce and 1 tablespoon mandarin syrup.
Toss together, refrigerate, serve on bed of bok choy.
Serves 4.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cheese Pastry:
Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup oleo soften to room temperature.
Blend together.
Stir in flour and chill about 1 hour.
Shape in 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased muffin pans.
Press dough against bottom and sides.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix together in large mixer bowl the eggs, sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add flour.
Then add apples and nuts.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hot breakfast dish
directions: Place croutons in 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs; add milk, sausage and dried mustard.
Pour over croutons.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Place all ingredients into food processor.
Pulsate until chopped fine. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all together and make into balls.
Mix remaining soup with 1 can of water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: mary's meat loaf
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Taste and adjust seasoning and bake in oven for about 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Bake in iron skillet if possible.

title: sweet and sour medley
directions: Combine preserves and barbecue sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Simmer until heated, stirring occasionally.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Mix all ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
Alternate mixture with tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O powder and whipped topping.
In a separate bowl, mix cottage cheese and mandarin oranges.
Combine the 2 mixtures. Refrigerate until set.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill for 30 minutes and serve.

title: country combo dip
directions: Mix together.
Garnish with crisp crumbled bacon.

title: blintzes with cheese
directions: Blend the ingredients until smooth.
Heat the frying pan. Pour batter into pan to cover the bottom.
Fry on one side until light brown, then other side.

title: kung pao pork
directions: Trim fat from the pork loin; cut pork into 3/4-inch pieces. Toss pork, 2 teaspoons cornstarch, the salt and white pepper in medium bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Cut bell pepper into 3/4-inch squares.
Cut green onions diagonally into 3/4-inch pieces.
Mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch, the sugar and broth.
